text:
#iwantasweetersociety!! this month is human trafficking awareness month & i'm supporting a fantastic australian-owned business @sweetsocietyapparel - that's combatting human trafficking by employing women who've been rescued, giving them meaningful employment and opportunity. 
human trafficking is everwhere. it's in our supply chains, it's in the world's domestic, travel, luxury & food services. vulnerable families and people are preyed upon, men and women walk into being trafficked without even realizing and people risk their life trying to reach safety through traffickers as well. it is a sick, enormous global trade. having worked with men, women and children who've been trafficked, i have seen the huge physical & psychological damage it can cause. 
i am fortunate to have met the founder of @sweetsocietyapparel, @e_emilyanne, last year in cambodia. i am constantly inspired by people, especially women, who dedicate their lives to contributing to the greater good, which is exctly what em is doing. show some love and support her page & business - everything you do, every purchase you make, can and does make a difference! thanks to em & the girls behind sweet society & here's to doing our bit for a better world 🌏

text:
odi has finally reached our 10-year milestone. we could not have done this without your support. male sexual abuse has a long lasting impact on men, especially men who are trying to navigate the social definition of masculinity. 
odi has been able to leave an imprint on the nyc community by providing free confidential support services to abuse survivors. we have also organized several panel discussions on the topic of male sexual abuse. in 2017 odi launched its monthly newsletter that addresses topics that impact male survivors. we had the largest photo exhibition of a diverse group of male survivors; phase two saw the inclusion of women. 
we ask that you join us in our celebration.  we are asking individuals to make a donation of $10 in support of our 10th anniversary. 
thank you 
dennis o tyson mpa
presdient & ceo (founder)
o'brien dennis intiative

text:
when the chaotic static of my mind caused me to feel overwhelmed with the mundane world he took my hand and sat with me smiling ever so encouragingly. "make a list," he said looking into my eyes, his gentle expression comforting me in the midst of an emotional storm. "start with writing down one 'to do' item and then leave a dash underneath...but leave it blank, for now.  finish your first task then gage how you feel, if you are able to go on then write down the next 'to do' item...you do not have to do more around here than you feel comfortable with.  you can't be overwhelmed by one task at a time." he is my rock, my stability in the midst of turmoil...he helps me in such simple ways while i learn to overcome ptsd.
.
#metoo #survivor #personalhealing #ptsd #mentalhealthawarness #witch #witchlife #witchwoman #witchsofinstagram #pagan #paganwoman #pagansofinstagram #theelementsfour

text:
#unewsupdates: alicia keys announced she’ll be hosting the 61st annual grammys 
alicia keys took to social media to announce that she’ll be hosting this year’s grammy award show. she posted a picture of herself holding a grammy and directed fans to her ig story where she spoke about how she got the opportunity and that she “knows what it’s like to be on that stage.” with 15 grammys under her belt already, safe to say she knows about what it takes to earn a grammy, and the feeling you get after you’ve done so. in the video, she also said she’s exited to bring her light and energy on stage. with everything happening in the culture like the #metoo movement, alicia said she wants to bring “sisterhood” vibes to the show.

she went on to say that she is really excited about her new gig and has “a lot in store.” would you be tuned in to watch alicia keys host the grammys? it will take place on february at the los angeles staples center.

so we expect something amazing😉

انترفيو شاه روخ مع صحيفه انديا اكسبرس ضمن ترويجات zero .. #الجزء_التالت 💥كيف قمت بالرومانسية في zero ... !؟ في هذا الفيلم ... هناك باوا يعانى من قصر قامته وفتاة على كرسي متحرك ... عندما بدأنا في تصويره ... أردنا البحث عن إجابة لسؤال .. هل يمكن أن تكون هناك مساواة بين هاتين الشخصيتين .. !؟ فكرنا .. ماذا تريد امرأة مثل عافية أن تشعر .. !؟ أنها لا تشعر بأنها أقل من أي شخص آخر .. بغض النظر عن الاختلافات بينهما هناك  مساواة بينهما .. 💙 
في افلامى السابقة لم تستطع ان تسألنى البطله عن هل تريد ان تقوم  بعلاقة رومانسية بشكل واضح ولكن هنا عافية تستطيع ان تسأل ...
هذة هى اعادة اختراع الرومانسية .. ان اقوم بشكل اخر من الرومانسية التى لم يتوقعها منى احد من قبل .. 💙 💥في حملة #metoo " حملة ضد التحرش في الهند " ما هي النصيحة التي من شأنها أن تعطيها لأي شخص حول الاعتداءات السلبية على الجنسين .. !؟ ثلاثة أشياء .. : (الاحترام .. والاحترام .. والاحترام .. )
ليس هناك حب ورومانسية دون احترام .. الاحترام يعني المساواة .. ولا أقصد المساواة التى على مواقع التواصل الاجتماعي "هاشتاج المساواة "

بالنسبة لي .. المساواة تتيح لك معرفة مدى ضعفك ، والمساواة  تسألك .. هل يمكنك أن تهتم بي .. !؟ هذا ما فعلته مع زوجتي .. وأصدقائي من النساء لأنني أحبهم حقًا .. 💙

أُعلم  ابني البالغ من العمر 21 عامًا أن عدم احترام شخص ما أمر غير مقبول .. ولا أعني الضرب أو  أى نوع من الاعتداءات التى اطلقتها حملة #metoo. أنا أتحدث عن الاحترام الأساسي .. 💙✋ لقد تزوجت منذ 30 عاما ولكني لم أقم أبدا بالنظر في حقيبة زوجتي .. ما زلت أدق عليها باب غرفة النوم إذا كان مغلق، وأطرق باب غرفة نوم ابنتي .. إنهم 
يعرفون أنه أنا .. لكن هذة هي مساحتهم الخاصة .. " 
#افتخر_كونك_فان_لانسان_عظيم 💪✋
#zerothefilm #katrinakaif #anushkasharma #shahrukhkhan #kingofacting👑 #srkmorocofan

text:
busy philips will always be synomous in my mind with kim kelly, the character she played in the glorious freaks and geeks but of course she is far more famous for being an instagram star. it's clear from her memoirs that she was destined or at the very least acutely determined to be famous. what sets her apart however is that she doesn't pull any punches in describing  how she broke into, survived and all but bowed out of the hollywood scene and it does leave you wondering why so many subject themselves to this perilous industry with it's endless rejection, body shaming and blatent and widespread sexism. this book harnesses the power of the #metoo movement and busy is forthright and cutthroat  in exposing many incidents of shameful behaviour she encountered/witnessed over the years. nobody is above being called out here. it is her description however of her earliest sexual encounter and the rape she suffered, a rape she wasn't even aware was rape until much later,  which i found most moving, reminding us of how we must continue to vigilent in our  discussions and educatation on the importance of consent. busy has been accused of being angry in this book and she is but she has every fucking right to be and she is highly entertaining to boot.
#thiswillonlyhurtalittle
#busyphilipps

name: Janice Moore
tweet_full:
busy philips will always be synomous in my mind with kim kelly, the character she played in the glorious freaks and geeks but of course she is far more famous for being an instagram star. it is clear from her memoirs that she was destined or at the very least acutely determined to be famous. what sets her apart however is that she does not pull any punches in describing  how she broke into, survived and all but bowed out of the hollywood scene and it does leave you wondering why so many subject themselves to this perilous industry with it is endless rejection, body shaming and blatent and widespread sexism. this book harnesses the power of the #metoo movement and busy is forthright and cutthroat  in exposing many incidents of shameful behaviour she encountered/witnessed over the years. nobody is above being called out here. it is her description however of her earliest sexual encounter and the rape she suffered, a rape she wasn't even aware was rape until much later,  which i found most moving, reminding us of how we must continue to vigilent in our  discussions and educatation on the importance of consent. busy has been accused of being angry in this book and she is but she has every fucking right to be and she is highly entertaining to boot.
#thiswillonlyhurtalittle
#busyphilipps

text:
“gillette chastises men in a new commercial highlighting the #metoo movement- and some are furious.” - @businessinsider ...ummm, what? the commercial i watched challenged men to hold themselves and each other to higher standards. *which isn’t something that’s solely applicable to men,* but in this commercial, yes, men are the target audience. 
i have a 20-month-old son, so the reminder that the next generation of men is watching meant something to me. my son is a strong, spirited individual, and i’m always going to encourage that creativity and drive. i’m also going to teach him to respect and stand up for those around him- whether it be a woman or otherwise. holding himself accountable and making no excuses for bad behavior will be the expectation in our home. if that’s considered “chastising” my son- sorry, not sorry. 🤷🏼‍♀️

text: hoy tuve la oportunidad de conocer a integrantes del equipo de logística del movimiento #metoo y #timeisup. estoy completamente admirada de la gestión y proceso que dedican a cada caso de acoso sexual que reciben. desde las denuncias de actrices en hollywood y otras industrias de entretenimiento, se realizó una campaña de recaudación para lograr asumir casos de personas que viven violencia y hostigamiento sexual en sus centros de trabajo y que no pueden financiar un proceso judicial. siempre pienso en paulo freire, desde tu metro cuadrado una puede hacer grandes transformaciones.

pt.7 🥃🍿👀robert sylvester kelly (born january 8, 1967)  is an american singer, songwriter, record producer, and former professional basketball player. a native of chicago, kelly began performing during the late 1980s and debuted in 1992 with the group public announcement. in 1993, kelly went solo with the album 12 play. he is known for a collection of major hit singles including "bump n' grind", "your body's callin'", "i believe i can fly", "gotham city", "ignition (remix)", "if i could turn back the hands of time", "the world's greatest", "i'm a flirt (remix)", and the hip-hopera "trapped in the closet". in 1998, kelly won three grammy awards for "i believe i can fly".his distinctive sound and style has influenced numerous hip hop and contemporary r&b artists. kelly became the first musician to play professional basketball, when he was signed in 1997.

text_retweet:
reposted from @yourrightscamp -  via thegrio.com: after two black men were found dead in democratic donor ed buck’s home within the last 18 months, a writer is coming forward to say that his list of alleged victims far exceeds what any of us could have imagined.
according to nbc news, six months ago jasmyne cannick posted a warning on her twitter that it would only be a matter of time before another man lost his life while feeding buck’s dangerous sexual proclivities.
“if another young, black gay man overdoses or worse dies at democratic donor ed buck’s apartment it’s going to be the fault of the sheriff’s dept and l.a. district atty for not stopping him when they had the opportunity to,” cannick wrote on twitter in late july.
after gemmel moore died from a methamphetamine overdose in buck’s apartment in july of 2017, cannick contacted moore’s friends and family, and discovered they’d found a rather detailed journal among his possessions. in the journal the 26-year-old outlined how buck got him hooked on meth and drugged him against his will.
in the last year cannick has conducted interviews with several men who said that buck offered them money to let him administer an injection of crystal methamphetamine into their bodies, which is the most dangerous way to take the drug...but cannick isn’t buying that explanation and wants the community to be put on notice that black men aren’t safe as long as buck is free. ...

text:
happy 2019 babies!!! finally feeling like myself and decided to introduce myself to the babes who are new to my space.
•
•
my name is davia (duh-vee-ya) and i'm a mental health educator and yoga teacher 🧘🏾‍♀️. you may know me as the host of the #affirmpodcast by @redefineenough. in the past, i've been a full time trauma counselor working with survivors of sexual assault and domestic violence.
•
•
currently, i consider myself a counselor on sabbatical and a social entrepreneur. in 2019, i'm traveling to festivals, conferences, and universities to teach activists, helping professionals, and companies about mental health, trauma, and sustainability in the workplace.
•
•
prepare yourself for yoga pics, bulldog memes, and wellness truth bombs (no cutesy selfcare fluff because you can get that anywhere.)
•
•
if you're new, say hi 👋🏾 and introduce yourself!
•
📸 @dalfranc

text:
#10yearchallenge
.
it may be hard to tell but a lot has changed in 10 years!
.
the girl on the left was so insecure. she was desperate to fit in and relied on other people’s approval. she never felt good enough no matter what she did.
.
in the external world, she thought she’d already been through the hardest thing ever - seeing her parents split up. she didn’t think it was her fault but she did create a lot of unworthiness around it.
.
little did she know that a few years later her brother would die. and then she’d be sexually assaulted. and then she’d lose control of her car on the highway and flip and roll into the ditch.
.
she didn’t know that her unworthiness and feelings of self-doubt would continue to bring about patterns in her life that kept her feeling unworthy. she didn’t understand why she kept attracting guys who didn’t really care about her or respect her.
.
she had no idea what the future had in store - but i can guarantee it ended up being something she never would’ve imagined.
.
there were also some amazing things in those 10 years... like traveling the world, working with elephants and other wildlife, studying various self-help programs, scuba diving in the philippines, meditating in the himalayas, understanding & healing her relationship with her dad, meeting some amazing people, and totally transforming her life! ✨
.
life is about growth and these 10 years really sum that up for me. the curveballs forced me to learn and grow in ways that most people don’t.
.
i went from full-fledged drowning to fighting my way back up to the surface to grab a breath of fresh air... to drowning again, to catching my breath, over and over again.
.
until finally i stayed above the water.
.
“release to thrive” came to me a couple months back because it’s what i did and what i teach my clients to do. that’s why it’s the name of my signature private coaching program, and also the name of my new podcast (coming soon hopefully 🤞🏽).
.
what do your past 10 years look like?! how much have you grown? tag me in your own 10 year challenge photo and use the hashtag #releasetothrive so i can see how you’ve overcome your challenges & share your story of growth! ☺️💕
name: Release Expert & Energy Healer

she didn’t know that her unworthiness and feelings of self-doubt would continue to bring about patterns in her life that kept her feeling unworthy. she didn’t understand why she kept attracting guys who didn’t really care about her or respect her.
.
she had no idea what the future had in store - but i can guarantee it ended up being something she never would’ve imagined.
.
there were also some amazing things in those 10 years... like traveling the world, working with elephants and other wildlife, studying various self-help programs, scuba diving in the philippines, meditating in the himalayas, understanding & healing her relationship with her dad, meeting some amazing people, and totally transforming her life! ✨
.
life is about growth and these 10 years really sum that up for me. the curveballs forced me to learn and grow in ways that most people don’t.
.
i went from full-fledged drowning to fighting my way back up to the surface to grab a breath of fresh air... to drowning again, to catching my breath, over and over again.
.
until finally i stayed above the water.
.
“release to thrive” came to me a couple months back because it’s what i did and what i teach my clients to do. that’s why it’s the name of my signature private coaching program, and also the name of my new podcast (coming soon hopefully 🤞🏽).
.
what do your past 10 years look like?! how much have you grown? tag me in your own 10 year challenge photo and use the hashtag #releasetothrive so i can see how you’ve overcome your challenges & share your story of growth! ☺️💕

text:
🥃🍿👀robert sylvester kelly (born january 8, 1967)  is an american singer, songwriter, record producer, and former professional basketball player. a native of chicago, kelly began performing during the late 1980s and debuted in 1992 with the group public announcement. in 1993, kelly went solo with the album 12 play. he is known for a collection of major hit singles including "bump n' grind", "your body's callin'", "i believe i can fly", "gotham city", "ignition (remix)", "if i could turn back the hands of time", "the world's greatest", "i'm a flirt (remix)", and the hip-hopera "trapped in the closet". in 1998, kelly won three grammy awards for "i believe i can fly".his distinctive sound and style has influenced numerous hip hop and contemporary r&b artists. kelly became the first musician to play professional basketball, when he was signed in 1997.

text: esse talvez seja meu post mais polêmico e controverso em todos esses anos no instagram ... mas vamos lá.. esse pensamento está me acompanhando desde toda a repercussão do movimento #metoo, expondo comportamentos abusivos nos bastidores de hollywood.. e isso está longe de ser qualquer tipo de defesa àqueles homens.. acho justo alguém se negar a trabalhar com um abusador ou estuprador. mas começou a preocupar quando começaram a julgar o trabalho pelos atos da pessoa. por exemplo o kevin spacey.. entendo alguem se recusar a trabalhar com ele desde as acusações de abuso dele.. mas algumas pessoas começaram a julgar os filmes anteriores a tudo isso. e isso não faz o menor sentido. não da pra dizer que o kevin spacey seja um ator ruim, mesmo que seja um lixo de ser humano. no mundo da interpretação, cinema e séries é difícil fazer essa separação.. como conviver com alguem que na vida pessoal abusou de alguém?? mas na #musica acho possível sim fazer essa separação. herivelto martins batia na mulher, a cantora dalva de oliveira. triste demais isso. hoje com certeza teria a punição que merecia. talvez ele não mereça, mas as obras dele tem que ser respeitadas . no caso do r. kelly. é facil apedrejar o cara, dizer que se arrependeu por ter trabalhado com ele.. e se for verdade tudo o que está sendo revelado, que que seja mesmo condenado, pague como pessoa fisica, mas a obra dele precisaria ser separada da pessoa fisica. e esse comentário não vem porque sou fá das musicas dele. mas o que tem por aí de músicos com boas musicas e com a vida pessoal questionável ou pior, com problemas pessoais que sequer vieram a publico... o mesmo canal que produziu o documentário expondo r.kelly está preparando outro documentário entrevistando os adultos que quando crianças frequentavam neverland. e se tudo o que sempre rolou há anos como boatos sobre o michael jackson vier a tona? as mesmas pessoas que hoje estão fingindo que nunca trabalharam com o r.kelly e que sempre declararam inspiração direta no mj terão a mesma atitude?

pt.2 🥃🍿👀robert sylvester kelly (born january 8, 1967)  is an american singer, songwriter, record producer, and former professional basketball player. a native of chicago, kelly began performing during the late 1980s and debuted in 1992 with the group public announcement. in 1993, kelly went solo with the album 12 play. he is known for a collection of major hit singles including "bump n' grind", "your body's callin'", "i believe i can fly", "gotham city", "ignition (remix)", "if i could turn back the hands of time", "the world's greatest", "i'm a flirt (remix)", and the hip-hopera "trapped in the closet". in 1998, kelly won three grammy awards for "i believe i can fly".his distinctive sound and style has influenced numerous hip hop and contemporary r&b artists. kelly became the first musician to play professional basketball, when he was signed in 1997.

text:
i mean...maybe it’s because i’m a woman, but i’m not all that offended by gillette’s new commercial. i find it condescending in a way, as it assumes all men behave badly and it comes across kinda preachy when their job is to sell shaving accessories. but i’d be lying if i said this topic is something that doesn’t require discussion. real talk, growing up as a young woman, i’ve definitely experienced boys/men cat calling, touching me inappropriately, making sexually explicit comments about my body/shape...the whole nine. every time i expressed anger or frustration about it, i was painted as being unreasonable because i should understand that this is just what boys/ men do. i was even told that one day when i’m older i’d look back and appreciate that attention because as an older woman i wouldn’t get it anymore! that’s madness!  while i am against today’s wave of feminism, which i believe is set up to utterly emasculate men, i am for treating women respectfully and for our being valued equally as human beings. 
with that said, i believe women must also carry ourselves respectfully and with dignity. knowing that there are some deranged men out there who will try us as women simply because they’re men is the very reason i cannot stand to see women exploit themselves! certainly, no matter what a woman wears, a man shouldn’t touch her! but knowing that some men are absolute idiots with no self control, it doesn’t make sense as a woman to make it that much easier (in that man’s mind) to come at her sideways. these types of men will take advantage of that! 
i hate that the #metoo movement and goofy initiatives like the “slut walk” have made it almost socially acceptable to demonize all men and paint all women as angelic victims. yet i also hate that for far too long society has turned a blind eye to certain behaviors from men as a normal part of being a man while telling women we’ve just got to deal with it.

so, no. i’m not offended by the commercial. but to be fair, we also need an ad to address self-respect in women and girls. not because a lack of self respect is an excuse for being disrespected...but because in this case it’s pretty much expected.

text:
here’s my story...since i could remember i was always the ugly duckling and was constantly harassed by boyfriends, ”friends” classmates, family, employers, coworkers , teachers etc. it seems that nothing has changed people still continue to act in hostile ways! whether it was calling me fat/ skinny , pitching my fat/ telling me i was looking sick, saying i’m not smart enough, that i speak to simplistic, that my pictures seemed photoshopped, that i’m showing too much of my body or i’m a bitch/slut... stop 🛑 shaming women! if you are so concern with others it’s because you guys are too insecure and need to work on yourself! i have been through the most difficult situations these past years, the only difference now is that i have selflove and have learned to love me regardless of how others see me! 
#eatingdisorder ✅ 
depression ✅ 
insercuity ✅ 
abuse ✅ 🌱🌱i am sharing my experience because the way that people act towards each other only leads to ( mental and physical damage / death). 🛑 shamming ... 🛑 think before you speak 🛑 think before you act🛑 we can all change the world! #metoo #metoomovement 🙏🏽❤️ i truly apologize if i have ever made any of you feel worthless, you are all incredible human beings and deserve respect!

text:
this is me, standing in front of the #newyork legislature in 2017, with all of the other brave advocates who were fighting for the rights of children and adult survivors of child sexual abuse. i know how important it is that @nygovcuomo passes the #childvictimsact in the next 30 days because children shouldn’t have to wait another moment to be protected on these streets. i was abused by my mother, a family member, and other people during the course of my lifetime. please show your support by calling gov. cuomo at tel: 1.518.474.8390 and urge him to pass the child victims act in the next 30 days. visit protectnykids.org for more info. 
last year, new yorkers made history at the polls by electing a democratic majority in the new york state senate.  through the efforts of dozens of coalitions and advocacy groups, in partnership with hundreds of community organizers and tens of thousands of grassroots activists -- new yorkers have changed the path of history. 
the fighting for children pac, which has been at the forefront of the effort to flip the new york senate for several years, anticipates that the passage of the child victims act will be one of the first orders of business for the next session of the new york legislature.  after passing the assembly several times in the past decade, the child victims act, which has been blocked from a vote in the formerly republican led state senate in every case, will likely finally be voted into law when the legislative session re-opens. 
but we need you to stand up and speak up for the children who are voiceless.

#metoo #timesup #kidstime #protectnykids #cuomo #newyork #legislation
name: Nikki DuBose
tweet_full:
this is me, standing in front of the #newyork legislature in 2017, with all of the other brave advocates who were fighting for the rights of children and adult survivors of child sexual abuse. i know how important it is that @nygovcuomo passes the #childvictimsact in the next 30 days because children shouldn’t have to wait another moment to be protected on these streets. i was abused by my mother, a family member, and other people during the course of my lifetime. please show your support by calling gov. cuomo at tel: 1.518.474.8390 and urge him to pass the child victims act in the next 30 days. visit protectnykids.org for more info. 
last year, new yorkers made history at the polls by electing a democratic majority in the new york state senate.  through the efforts of dozens of coalitions and advocacy groups, in partnership with hundreds of community organizers and tens of thousands of grassroots activists -- new yorkers have changed the path of history. 
the fighting for children pac, which has been at the forefront of the effort to flip the new york senate for several years, anticipates that the passage of the child victims act will be one of the first orders of business for the next session of the new york legislature.  after passing the assembly several times in the past decade, the child victims act, which has been blocked from a vote in the formerly republican led state senate in every case, will likely finally be voted into law when the legislative session re-opens. 
but we need you to stand up and speak up for the children who are voiceless.

#metoo #timesup #kidstime #protectnykids #cuomo #newyork #legislation

text:
along the lines of the question, “how good are you willing to let it be?” is the question, “what am i tolerating?” because if it drains you, doesn’t inspire you, doesn’t light you up or quicken your heart rate...it doesn’t belong in your life. 
and you may have a blind spot and not even notice how a situation is draining you.  or justifying its place in your life- so then what?

find someone you trust, who knows you and what you’re up to for them to point it out. 
cuz when you remove one thing a week? whether that be clothes that don’t fit, a friendship that isn’t serving either of you or sugar-one thing a week leads to massive growth 
we got this

text:
i remember watching the women’s march that occurred in january 2017 with tingles down my arms and tears in my eyes. i was astounded that so many women had left their homes to march in protest against being harassed, victimized, abused and assaulted. i was in awe of their bravery to speak up and use their voices to express their frustrations and to feel empowered. but i was also really saddened to see how many women had been victimized and hurt without any justice, without anyone to believe them or any comfort.
.
many women are finally coming forward and breaking their silence to divulge being victimized by powerful men and then being shamed into covering it up. it’s an amazing moment to witness in history and to be a part of. so how should christians respond? sometimes, in the midst of a major shift in culture, christians find it easier to stay silent (waving my hand around here because hello i’ve been guilty of that!) and change the topic. it can be hard to know how to make your voice heard.
.
this week's blog post is all about how i think christians can do a better job at responding to this major cultural shift and be an extension of the hands and feet of christ.
.
what do you think is the best way for christians to respond? let me know in the comments and full post is linked in my bio!
.
.

text:
dear ig, moving forward - can we please do the work of ending our conscious and unconscious investments in patriarchy and misogyny? it’s easier said then done, but the investments and subsequent damages have to stop with us. womxn of color and girls of color have historically been the receptacles for racialized and gendered fantasies of us as either - always wanting it, not wanting it enough, passive recipients of the d or anything else, objects to be perused through, too emotional to be logical, bitches who complain too much, and/or too cocky when we stand up for ourselves or our communities. we are imagined and positioned to be receptacles. when we stand tall (especially from within) and fight back - we are too much. instead, we are supposed to be obedient and quiet girls (just to take it). see: how we were imagined during histories and current versions of colonization, imperialist wars, chattel slavery. think about the ways we, as a racialized hetero world - are invested in these characterizations of femmes of all genders. and what we do to maintain these fantasies as reality. how often do we hear, “don’t be a bitch?” or “she’s a bitch” - b/c she said, “not today.” or he’s a bitch, because he doesn’t subscribe to hypermasculinity or has her back. and what ends up the material, lived consequences of these obsessive fantasies? see: physical, sexual, emotional, financial violence. how often do we actually believe being a bitch means weakness? i’ve been called a bitch in so many contexts that i have learned to say (in the words of redman), “i’ll be that.” smash, divest, fuck up patriarchy. and do it first by taking inventory in the ways we are invested and implicated in it. all love and fight. for freedom, doc wun w/ you. when we know better, we do better. let’s do better together. 
#aapiwomenlead #insolidarity #womenofcolor #metoo #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #eachoneteachone #timesup #abolition #docwun #teamsmakedreams #smashpatriarchy .
(image description: person with hijab and fist up center with “smash patriarchy”).
name: Dr. Connie Wun
tweet_full:
dear ig, moving forward - can we please do the work of ending our conscious and unconscious investments in patriarchy and misogyny? it’s easier said then done, but the investments and subsequent damages have to stop with us. womxn of color and girls of color have historically been the receptacles for racialized and gendered fantasies of us as either - always wanting it, not wanting it enough, passive recipients of the d or anything else, objects to be perused through, too emotional to be logical, bitches who complain too much, and/or too cocky when we stand up for ourselves or our communities. we are imagined and positioned to be receptacles. when we stand tall (especially from within) and fight back - we are too much. instead, we are supposed to be obedient and quiet girls (just to take it). see: how we were imagined during histories and current versions of colonization, imperialist wars, chattel slavery. think about the ways we, as a racialized hetero world - are invested in these characterizations of femmes of all genders. and what we do to maintain these fantasies as reality. how often do we hear, “don’t be a bitch?” or “she’s a bitch” - b/c she said, “not today.” or he’s a bitch, because he doesn’t subscribe to hypermasculinity or has her back. and what ends up the material, lived consequences of these obsessive fantasies? see: physical, sexual, emotional, ficial violence. how often do we actually believe being a bitch means weakness? i’ve been called a bitch in so many contexts that i have learned to say (in the words of redman), “i’ll be that.” smash, divest, fuck up patriarchy. and do it first by taking inventory in the ways we are invested and implicated in it. all love and fight. for freedom, doc wun w/ you. when we know better, we do better. let’s do better together. 
#aapiwomenlead #insolidarity #womenofcolor #metoo #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #eachoneteachone #timesup #abolition #docwun #teamsmakedreams #smashpatriarchy .
(image description: person with hijab and fist up center with “smash patriarchy”).

text:
warning! this is a really long one guys, but here goes... i sat at my grandmothers kitchen table this last weekend, and she made a simple statement that really resonated with me. she said “i don’t remember getting old. i was busy doing things and the years just went by”. that really hit me. before you know it, the time is lost. so often too many of us are stagnant, just letting the time go by; i’ve been one of these people far too often. none of us know if we have a tomorrow, we can’t take so many things and especially people for granted. we can’t ever get time passed back, and we need to focus on what truly matters. 
so, that brings me to this. it is late, (oh shush i know, typical me!) but, new years...new year resolutions. i’ve always been a bit negative about them. “people set expectations too far out of reach”, “that’s not going to happen”, “you’re setting yourself up for failure”, “it won’t last past january”. it’s just another year, another number, a different date; it means nothing. then came 2018... if you would like, you can scroll down and read the rest in the comments below ⬇️

text:
i watched this, this morning and was left speechless, which seldom ever happens.  i had to share so i’m gonna drop this right here.
side note: men, please, please don’t do away with one of my favorite things in the world, your masculinity.  please continue with your manly man thing, women (the normal majority) love it and we love you!  there is no “toxic masculinity.” it’s a newly minted, ginned up term by millennials – the term itself is toxic.  it’s simple really, in layman’s terms, there are men who are assholes and there are men who are not.  don’t be an asshole.  there.  problem solved.  stay classy and masculine!
**same applies to women.  i actually know more women assholes than men if i’m being honest.  see how i even made this gender inclusive?👫
.

text:
hidden issues of sexual harassment [series]: first, you are in shock… and disbelief. how could someone whom you trust and respect behave inappropriately toward you? you worry you could be misinterpreting, but there’s no denying the truth… this is sexual harassment. so now, what to do? always ask -tell- them to stop. maybe they will, or it may get better for awhile… or worse.
•
next, your allegiances are torn. you’re a great employee and not one to stir up problems, but you decide to do the right thing and report. you ask for protection within the organization. but instead of protection, that’s when everything explodes. you feel disbelieved ~ anything but supported. false accusations may be directed against you and coworkers may ostracize you. three of four who report harassment experience retaliation.  you may be blackballed and asked/forced to leave against your will.
•
“institutional betrayal” happens when the company or any other organization, maybe even your church, “fails to protect you at a time when you might reasonably expect it to. like betrayal trauma, institutional betrayal can lead to mental and physical harm.” [jennifer freyd & pamela birrell, “blind to betrayal”]
•
the initial betrayal by your harasser was bad enough, but now the organization has turned against you. your livelihood and career are collapsing in front of you. this is institutional betrayal, and statistics show it’s a common response to reports of sexual harassment. if you [or someone you know] is trapped in such a situation – realize this is abuse: stay calm, take notes, and seek legal consultation specialized in workplace law within the jurisdiction of your state as soon as possible to guide you to wise decisions.
•
if this isn’t you, how can you help? listen, support, never judge, never turn away - understand that a brave reporter now finds it hard to trust and feel safe. provide a job reference. connect the abuse survivor to a better career opportunity. help make others aware of the hidden injustices that result from harassment to stop it in the workplace... and the church.

text:
here are some of the faces of the survivors of abuse from r. kelly. 
another factor that played into this situation was people's instinct to separate the art from the artist. it turns out r. kelly's release of "i believe i can fly" and "i wish" were very calculated. he intentionally released songs at times where his reputation was under fire so that listeners would generally think of him with positive regard. he wanted people to be singing his songs in church so that they would later say "r. kelly? no way. he's so talented. my family loves his songs". we have a tendency to think that talent and genius = good person. .
so i have a challenge for us! stop separating the art from the artist. we started last year with hollywood and the #metoo movement. let's continue it with the music industry. i'm guilty of it too. i've idolized michael jackson my entire life, but guess who is featured in the next documentary of this kind? the "pretty young thing" star. .
#muterkelly #blacklivesmatter #sexualhealthwithdee #stopseparatingartfromartist #survivingrkelly #groomingawareness #manipulationawareness #abuseawareness #blackgirlsmatter

teenage pregnancies on decline.

text:
les personnes qui croient encore que le souci, c'est #rkelly, malgré toutes mes explications et mes prédictions . 
vous ratez le coche et c'est pour ça que j'insiste sur ce sujet depuis. mon unique souci, c'est l'heritage de la musique noire et il se trouve que robert en possède à lui seul, un des plus gros..
il peut aller en prison pour être jugé si on fournit des preuves.. mais
le révisionnisme musical, c'est-à-dire le fait de supprimer des chansons selon les actes posés (ici en plus présumés) par un artiste est une jurisprudence horrible.
"j'ai fait une chanson avec lui. 10 ans après, il bat sa femme ou en tue une .. ah non, je supprime la chanson". mystikal est en prison, parce qu'il a violé 2 femmes... on va supprimer ses chansons?
#nelly est accusé de 4 viols. on va supprimer ses titres? ( d'ailleurs les femmes du mouvement #metoo lui disent en com instagram qu'après r.kelly, c'est lui)
et au-délà des agressions sexuelles, #remyma avait tiré sur une femme et a fait 6 ans de prison. que va t-on faire des artistes qui ont commis des crimes? 
on va bannir les chansons de bobbybrown parce qu'il battait #whitneyhouston?
#tupac parce qu'il a fait de la prison pour viol? on va bientot nous dire aussi qu'il ne faut plus écouter 2pac... vu qu'on revise l'histoire de la musique avec des codes de 2019.

et je cite les artistes noirs, car l'éclairage sera sur eux principalement.
celine dion ne supprimerait jamais un duo avec elvis presley. tout comme personne ne supprimera les chansons de drluke et de plein d'autres.
personne n'a demandé de supprimer noir desir alors que cantat a tué marie trintignant et poussé sa seconde femme au suicide.. pour ne citer que ça!

les gens n'arrivent pas à voir sur le très long terme. ils se focalisent sur le fait qu'on leur ait dit " pedophile ( sans tribunal)", mais je vous explique que les retombées de cette police avec le coupable désigné vont créer un climat absolument délétère.
le mieux, ce serait même que robert aille en prison .. comme ça, ça poussera certains à reflechir... et à voir que la porte qu'ils ont ouvert musicalement va engouffrer la black music.
nous sommes juste au début !

triste réalité!

text:
#metoo merch – social justice kids: the white mom’s guide to making a difference in not-so-diverse schools
#
today's best price:  get it on amazon! is your white child prepared to stand up for racial justice at school? or will their silence send a message to marginalized kids that says: “i don’t care enough to speak up.” we all want to believe that our kids would do the right thing – stand in solidarity with kids who are being treated badly because of their race, gender, sexual orientation – but what are we doing to make sure they know how? do you feel alone in your sense of urgency to give your kids the tools to do better? this book inspires a bigger vision for children’s lifelong success in culturally vibrant groups. dr. mollie monahan brings 20+ years of experience working on equity and inclusion with students at predominantly white educational institutions. a pk-12 parent in a predominantly white school district herself, she now partners with other parents, teachers, and district leadership, increasing kids’ cultural competencies prior to graduation. in this book, you will:· learn exactly what will hold your child back from being a competent member of our diverse world;· pinpoint the barriers that keep teachers and district staff from investing in effective equity and diversity…

text:
how they used dr. mlk to decieve the world! #facts
orgies among the congregation 
among its other accusations are that:

dr king took part in "drunken sex orgies" and coerced young women to participate

he had love affairs with at least four women, including folk singer joan baez

the list of alleged indiscretions would likely have been deeply problematic for the civil rights leader if it had been made public in 1968.
⬇️
from 1870 to 1955 schools like dunbar high school in washington dc equaled or scored higher on standardized test scores than white schools.
from 1890 to 1950 every census report showed blacks at a higher participation rate in employment than whites.
in 1950 72% of black men had been married.
in 1950 81% of black women had been married.
teenage pregnancies on decline.
black poverty was on the decline.
less black families were on government assistance.
black income was on the rise for black population in comparison to whites.
in 1965 76.4% of black children were born to married women.
source @americanthinker.com

history 101: the cia & drugsthe cia has a long and sordid history with drug traffickers. and it’s all in the congressional record.
source
http://www.motherjones.com/politics/1998/06/history-101-cia-drugs/

the french connection was a scheme through which heroin was smuggled from turkey to france and then to the united states through canada. the operation reached its peak in the late 60s and early 70s, and was responsible for providing the vast majority of the heroin used in the u.s

crack cocaine 
for the better part of a decade, a bay area drug ring sold tons of cocaine to the crips and bloods street gangs of los angeles and funneled millions in drug profits to a latin american guerilla army run by the u.s. central intelligence agency source@oigjustoc.gov

text:
a broad women’s movement has emerged through the giant marches of the past two years, initially characterized by on-line explosions like #metoo. now, google and mcdonald’s workers have taken the movement forward through strike actions against sexual harassment. we must organize to defend and extend reproductive rights, win medicare for all, and fight workplace harassment. 
unfortunately, the strategy of the mainstream women’s organizations of closely aligning with the democratic party establishment has been a decisive failure for reproductive justice. 
we must build independent organizations relying on the strength of working ppl to fight for our rights. right now, the la teachers @utlanow are on strike. what if women broadly radicalized in this period joined in mass action with #redfored? 
wouldn’t it be great if the women’s marches scheduled for saturday turned into a national day of action? support striking teachers, no to the democrats caving on racist wall funding, back pay for all furloughed federal works...no need to negotiate with ourselves, let’s organize to fight capitalism’s race to the bottom. join up with @socialist_alternative minnesota on saturday, let’s march and discuss how to fight for a just, socialist world ✨👊
.
.
.

text:
hey dysphoric trans girl,
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i see you. your outfit is really cute today, and i’m really proud of you for getting out of bed with such grace.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the weight of dysphoria is heavy; let us help you carry it. you’re essential to the world we live in. you’re more than a trending topic. your body’s existence is a radical act and it’s survival is worthy of celebration.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
disappointment sucks; being able to still be disappointed means you are engaged in your life. you are an active player. that’s good!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
every part of you is a girl; especially the part you don’t like today. your voice, hands, and feet are feminine. what else could they be?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i love you,
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
a dysphoric trans girl.

text: truthfully, i actually wasn’t going to join in on this #10yearchallenge thing, but then i decided to say “fuck it, why not?” and do it anyways 🤷‍♀️ so here it is, approximately 10 years apart 🥂 miranda on the left: march 20th 2009, enjoying my 21st birthday 🎂 with friends at a fancy restaurant in vail, my first winter living in colorado 🏔... (almost) 10 years later ⏰ miranda on the right: picture is just a selfie 🤳 i took of myself this past christmas 2018 🎄 still living and loving life in colorado 🏔 but now 10 years later, i’m 30 (almost 31) a wife 💍 mama to an amazing 6 year old boy 👦🏼 (& dog mom 🐕 to our goofy pup tank) but i am also so so much more than that! 📣 i am also now a #warrior #survivor #healing from multiple sexual-violence-traumas, living/struggling daily with #ptsd 💔 and i am a voice for the voiceless 🤐🤭 sharing my truth and my story and standing with all survivors saying #metoo ✊🏼 and i’m also a #yoga 🤸‍♀️ and #meditation 🧘‍♀️ lover 🥰 geographically not much has changed, still living in beautiful colorado 🏔 but other than that, a lot has changed in the past 10 years! 🥂 miranda on the left was way less comfortable in her own skin, wore makeup 💄 regularly because she was convinced she wasn’t beautiful or “good enough” without it, and she still had a lot of growing and learning and evolving to do, (and i still do 😉) and that’s totally ok, that was just where i was in my life at that time/part of my journey, and that’s just where i needed to be then! as i am now exactly where i need to be today/right now ✅ miranda on the right, me right now, the 30 year old mom, still just as beautiful, still just as worthy, still enough, just as i am. it’s taken a long time to see that, but here i am now, full of acceptance and love for myself, just as i am. it’s not always perfect “self-love” and i’m not always fully in-love with myself as i’d like to be, but over the past 10 years, i’ve come a long way from 21 year old miranda on the left, and everyday i’m doing my best to really love myself, flaws, scars, ugly/painful past, fears, struggles, imperfections, and all 🔥 both versions of me are just as they are meant to be, perfectly imperfect, as we all are ♥️🙏🏼😘
name: 🦄Miranda🦋Joy🐺

among its other accusations are that:

dr king took part in "drunken sex orgies" and coerced young women to participate

the list of alleged indiscretions would likely have been deeply problematic for the civil rights leader if it had been made public in 1968.

from 1870 to 1955 schools like dunbar high school in washington dc equaled or scored higher on standardized test scores than white schools.
from 1890 to 1950 every census report showed blacks at a higher participation rate in employment than whites.

in 1950 81% of black women had been married.
teenage pregnancies on decline.
black poverty was on the decline.
less black families were on government assistance.
black income was on the rise for black population in comparison to whites.
in 1965 76.4% of black children were born to married women.

text:
how they used dr. mlk to decieve the world! #facts
orgies among the congregation 
among its other accusations are that:

dr king took part in "drunken sex orgies" and coerced young women to participate

he had love affairs with at least four women, including folk singer joan baez

the list of alleged indiscretions would likely have been deeply problematic for the civil rights leader if it had been made public in 1968.
⬇️
from 1870 to 1955 schools like dunbar high school in washington dc equaled or scored higher on standardized test scores than white schools.
from 1890 to 1950 every census report showed blacks at a higher participation rate in employment than whites.
in 1950 72% of black men had been married.
in 1950 81% of black women had been married.
teenage pregnancies on decline.
black poverty was on the decline.
less black families were on government assistance.
black income was on the rise for black population in comparison to whites.
in 1965 76.4% of black children were born to married women.
source @americanthinker.com

history 101: the cia & drugsthe cia has a long and sordid history with drug traffickers. and it’s all in the congressional record.
source
http://www.motherjones.com/politics/1998/06/history-101-cia-drugs/

the french connection was a scheme through which heroin was smuggled from turkey to france and then to the united states through canada. the operation reached its peak in the late 60s and early 70s, and was responsible for providing the vast majority of the heroin used in the u.s

crack cocaine 
for the better part of a decade, a bay area drug ring sold tons of cocaine to the crips and bloods street gangs of los angeles and funneled millions in drug profits to a latin american guerilla army run by the u.s. central intelligence agency source@oigjustoc.gov

the latest federal bureau of prisons statistics showed the white population was 58.7%. #mlk #survivingmlk #deception #martinlutherkingjr #economics #projectwakeyoassup #artist #civilrights #mickjagger #instagood #king #entertainment #sex #jeffreyepstein  #marvingaye #hughhefner  #musicindustry #elvispresley #pedophile #lawyer #judge #culture  #molestation #metoo

text:
🙌🏻instagram, 🎬film buffs, 👯‍♀️friends, 🙋🏽‍♂️anyone with an opinion- i need your help! —————————————————-
my new film “dirty girl” follows the story of a young woman after a brutal sexual assault. after escaping, she find solace in an unsuspected way- a group of women (true survivors) who give her the courage to speak out about what’s happened.
—————————————————
your opinion- without having seen the film, but hearing the longline, which of these posters tells that story best? which speaks to you and evokes strong emotion and desire to see the film? 1,2 or 3
—————————————————

text:
is this you?

we could have a to-do list with 9 out of 10 tasks ticked off and we would still obsess about the 1 that isn't done rather than acknowledge the amount of work we have completed. especially for women, we tend to be harder on ourselves and give ourselves less credit for work done. .
.
here's something you should know, your ability to appreciate who you are and what you have accomplished, affects the overall quality of your life. you must learn to enjoy the small steps you have made in the right direction and give yourself a pat on the back to say well done, so you can see the beauty and strength that has always been in you.
.
.
in my sitting room, the message on my clock says live, love, laugh as a daily reminder to focus on what is most important everyday and in every situation. 
this is your reminder to do same
.
.
you are deeply loved ❤️
.
.
#selftalkmatters #enjoyeachmoment
#youareenough #welldone #progressing #notperfect #justenough #braveheart #boldandbeautiful #strongandsexy #soulspeakcircle

эффективное продвижение в инстаграмм
❗️в instagram есть деньги и мы это доказали на своих клиентах и кейсах. рассказали об этом в прямом эфиры и все результаты публикуем в профиле.
❓но что делать тебе, чтобы зарабатывать деньги через instagram ?
есть два варианта:
1. найти хорошее smm агенство связаться с их клиентами и узнать результаты.
2. научиться самому
🔝второй вариант самый лучший, потому как после обучения ты сможешь грамотно оценить эффективность своего подрядчика и сможешь быстро среагировать на любую динамику.
👨🏻‍💻и как раз мы создали такой курс: «insta-education”, после прохождения такого курса вы станете экспертом в мире instagram, мы настолько уверенны в его качестве, что гарантируем возврат в случае отсутствия результата!
❗️полную программу ты можешь посмотреть перейдя по ссылке в шапке профиля и выбери раздел «обучающий курс по эффективной работе в инстаграмм» ❗️тебе придёт программа и если ты захочешь купить, мы пришлём тебе первый урок бесплатно

still think it was about #rkelly ? there have been over 200,000 minor marriages! america doesn't give a damn about women especially black women!!!!!!!!!! #rizzaislam #metoo #rizzanews #rizzawithfacts #rizzagotfacts #intellectualxtremist #intellectualxtremists #wefollowfarrakhan #revolutionary #nationofislam #nationbeenwoke #elijahmuhammad #farrakhan #malcolmx #blackwoman #blackman #ageofinformation #whitesupremacy

yaw think he lion ... peep it like issa real article, "over 5,500 people were granted approval to bring spouses or fiancées under the age of 18 into the country between 2007 and 2017. (the statistics are calculated over fiscal, not calendar, years.) and more than 2,900 minors were given permission to bring older spouses into the country in the same decade, according a report from the senate homeland security committee released friday. in almost every case, the younger person in the relationship was female.

approval of the immigration requests was legal, as the immigration and nationality act does not have age restrictions, according to the associated press.

until 2018, all u.s. states permitted child marriage. last year, new jersey and delaware banned all marriage before 18, according to reuters.
each year, 12 million girls around the world are married before age 18, according to girls not brides. "my passport ruined my life," said naila amin, who had dual citizenship in pakistan and the u.s., where she grew up. amin said she was engaged at 8 years old and she was forced into marriage in pakistan when she was 13. she applied for immigration papers for her husband, who was 13 years older than her. "i was a passport to him. they all wanted him here, and that was the way to do it," she said. text:
‘what i know for sure is that speaking our truth is the most powerful tool we have…..for too long women have not been heard or believed if they dare to speak the truth to the power of those men. but their time is up!’’ oprah

it’s been just over a year since the #metoo movement was created. as a result, more and more women have felt the courage to own, and voice, their stories, to reveal their pain and growth. to show true vulnerability and courage to reveal just how raw, messy and real life can be sometimes.

more and more women are starting to share the stories of their lives which aren’t perfect, beautiful, filtered or adapted for the masses.

more and more women are waking up, growing in strength, growing in courage. no longer willing to remain silent or play small.

this is my reminder to you that you should rise up and reveal your truth. speak out against hate, judgement or bias.

together, we can create change.

here’s to fierce, feminine leadership in action, where we use our collective voices to influence positive social change.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytic until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
slowly but surely, r. kelly is being erased from the internet. following decisions from lady gaga and céline dion to remove their kelly collaborations from streaming amid the fallout from renewed interest in his alleged sexual abuse, other artists are scrubbing him from their digital discographies, too.

tmz reports that chance the rapper, ciara, and the pussycat dolls are all in the process of getting rid of their kelly collaborations. after being quoted in surviving r. kelly, chance released a statement saying it was a “mistake” to work with kelly on 2015’s “somewhere in paradise.” “[t]he truth is any of us who ever ignored the r. kelly stories, or ever believed he was being setup/attacked by the system (as black men often are) were doing so at the detriment of black women and girls,” he said. that track has now reportedly been disabled on spotify.

reps on behalf of ciara also released a statement revealing the “level up” singer has also requested that sony take she and kelly’s 2006 collab “promise (go and get your tickets mix)” off streaming and itunes. interestingly, kelly’s parent label sony has remained mum on all matters r. kelly, though it’s said to be stonewalling his attempts to release new music on rca. tmz also claims that the pussycat dolls have asked interscope to yank 2008’s “out of this club” from all streaming. meanwhile, the video for dion’s duet with kelly, “i’m your angel,” has disappeared from youtube, though the song still remains on streaming for the time being. neither dion, ciara, nor the pussycat dolls have commented on kelly or the status of their respective collabs. kelly is currently under investigation in two states, with new york potentially joining next.

reps on behalf of ciara also released a statement revealing the “level up” singer has also requested that sony take she and kelly’s 2006 collab “promise (go and get your tickets mix)” off streaming and itunes. interestingly, kelly’s parent label sony has remained mum on all matters r. kelly, though it’s said to be stonewalling his attempts to release new music on rca. tmz also claims that the pussycat dolls have asked interscope to yank 2008’s “out of this club” from all streaming. meanwhile, the video for dion’s duet with kelly, “i’m your angel,” has disappeared from youtube, though the song still remains on streaming for the time being. neither dion, ciara, nor the pussycat dolls have commented on kelly or the status of their respective collabs. kelly is currently under investigation in two states, with new york potentially joining next.

text:
in the wake of the #metoo movement, #sexualassault has been a frequently discussed topic in recent months. the growing awareness of the problem has helped to bring many cases out of the dark, and encouraged #survivors to bring charges against their #abusers. it is important for #victims of sexual assault to get the help they need to heal and recover. it is also vital that they understand their rights and how to obtain help if they decide to take #legal action against the perpetrator.

sexual assaults can have devastating effects on victims, including both physical harm and mental and emotional #trauma. these attacks are never something to take lightly or to sweep under the rug. it is a terrible situation to be faced with, and it can leave victims feeling alone, afraid, and unsure of what to do.

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farage’s nod to steve bannon certainly hasn’t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analytica’s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses people’s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firm’s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trump’s campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue

text:
based on his provocative and popular @nytimes op-ed, the man they wanted me to be is both memoir and cultural analysis. jared yates sexton alternates between an examination of his working-class upbringing and historical, psychological, and sociological sources that examine the genesis of toxic masculinity and its consequences for society. •
as progressivism changes american society, and globalism shifts labor away from traditional manufacturing, the roles that have been prescribed to men since the industrial revolution have been rendered obsolete. donald trump’s campaign successfully leveraged male resentment and entitlement, and now, with trump as president and the rise of the #metoo movement, it’s clear that our current definitions of masculinity are outdated and even dangerous. •
the man they wanted me to be will be available from @counterpointpress may 2019.

text:
new blog on website - when men just don't know any better?
a few weeks ago i was approached with a job opportunity for an accounting position. i’ve been out of work for a while and i’m in desperate need because my finances are dwindling down. so, when i was approached with a possible job for a major social media influencer in beverly hills, i was thrilled and relieved. not only did the position seem perfect and i was qualified based on my experience, the pay was exactly what i was requesting and needed. the recruiter thought i’d be a perfect candidate, too. i had to do some testing though before i was sent out for an interview. and, even though i had been approached on a late afternoon i was willing to do whatever was required of me. that evening i researched the employer. the name had sounded familiar but i couldn’t pinpoint who he was. as he came across my screen, i totally knew who he was. i watched a few videos, googled him to see what others said about him, and checked out his instagram which displayed him dancing with several girls, other posts were he flaunted his mansion and cars but said that wasn’t what he valued. he values knowledge (on how to grow your instagram account?). was i really this desperate? he annoyed me and i really didn’t know what he does besides selling falsehoods and everything that is superficial and shallow.
i guess i was that desperate. i have no one helping me out. i don’t have much in my savings, no retirement, nothing really. i had to push my personal thoughts aside. i knew i had dealt with different personalities, probably equivalent or worse. i could do this, i thought. so the next morning i started on the two personality tests and a comprehension test. i began the first personality test. 100 questions, choice questions (either or) to see where your personality was on different aspects, were you a narcissist or not, etc. ugh. this was getting tedious and weird. 
cont....

text:
so this is a clip from the #gillette ad which has rendered @thepiersmorgan and hundreds of thousands of others apoplectic . they see it as an attack on ‘masculinity’, another assault by swivel-eyed feminists determined to belittle the male species. 
its sad how quickly we divide into two camps- them and us, women against men.

i guess perspective is everything but when i watch the advert, i just don’t see what piers and his friends see. 
i see it as being about creating a better environment for everybody -regardless of gender- but, perhaps especially for men . 
surely ,it’s not about quashing masculinity but expanding and redefining masculinity?

getting rid of the macho strait jacket which forces little boys to hold back the tears , to sit on their feelings , to put on a brave face, to be ‘one of the guys’. all of those traditional stereotypes which most mental health charities agree contribute to the fact that suicide is the biggest killer of men under the age of 45
i am blessed to have and have had  many strong, capable, fearless men in my life but they’ve also been vulnerable at times, scared , unsure, in need of a shoulder to cry on .we need to give them space and permission to express that to themselves and each other and, with that freedom , they will be the best that they can be.

what do you see? .
.
.

#gillette #giletteadvert #metoo #metoomovement #masculinity #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness @gilletteuk

text:
#10yearschallenge 
the hands of time have done a #metoo on my face and ravaged it: it has been an eventful decade. 
i’m supposed to say that ‘i love every line and relish every wrinkle, because it all came from love and laughter.’ the truth is the only reason i haven’t had botox yet is because i’m worried it’ll leak into my breast milk and turn jesse into a lizard or something. (#mamxiety)

but once he’s off the boob and on the bolognese properly, it’ll be a forehead as big and bouncy as a barker and stonehouse cushion for me. 
#motherhoodunplugged #mamface #bodyimage

text:
after a few questions i saw that this was his very own personality test. why i knew, they were coming from his website and i had taken personality tests before. some of these questions seemed different. more personal. and that was just it. they kept getting more personal. some questions were building upon each other, making me feel more uncomfortable as i continued. probably 50 questions in i just wanted to stop. was he serious? what he is asking is wrong. i can’t recall what number this question was, i must have been more than halfway through when one of my choices were – ‘i enjoy having sex with people i hardly know’. oh my gosh! i’m done, i thought. all kinds of emotions were happening. was he serious? in this age of #timesup and #metoo, doesn’t he know better?
in the end of drilling through the rest of his personality test with a bunch of, “that’s none of your business”, stopping at should i choose – ‘my body is nothing special’ or ‘i like to look at my body’, i completed the test and the other test, too. i sat for a minute trying to decide what i what i was 
going to do. should i just follow through and see what happens? maybe i can confront him face to face. i emailed the recruiter. i declined the position because i found his questions inappropriate, i wrote. she later called me to discuss and apologized. i never responded.
being an older woman who was raised with no gender roles, where i could do just about everything a man could do and vice versa, i wonder why things are still so unequal? i recognize the beauty i had especially in my twenties in the bright lights of hollywood and learned the hard way what that gets you. i’ve made myself too aware of the statistics of crime against women inflicted by men and in my belief the crime is also being committed everyday by keeping women down, economically and socially. i became a very capable independent woman and mother that raised a young man to not see women as less than because she has different body parts.
this behavior of inappropriateness has happened for centuries where women are an object. 
cont...

text:
gillette what just happened here..?
this new advert has divided opinion unlike anything i’ve seen for a while.
.
here’s my take:
.
there’s a potentially uplifting message here - but it gets lost. the way this has been put together (in my opinion) is a classic example of a failure to strike the right tone. instead of inspiring, it has offended. instead of uniting, it has spectacularly divided.
.
and the message i’m referring to is a message for people, all of us. we can all treat each other better, we can all step in when we see wrongdoing, bullying, harassment. we can all take a good look at ourselves in the mirror and be good examples to our children.
.
of course there are men who need to be held accountable for their actions, just as there are women who need to be held to account for theirs. in implying the problems lie with #masculinity as a whole, men ‘en masse’ rather than specific individuals, you are in danger of being perceived to attack the very people who buy your products.
.
was it worth the risk? it’s certainly the centre of attention. interested to hear others’ thoughts...
.
#gillette #editors #filmmakers #adsgonewrong #anypublicityisgoodpublicity #intentional #mentoo #metoo #weareallaccountable #opinionwriting

text:
연극 <나쁜자석> 불매합니다. (구)악어컴퍼니 (현)레드앤블루는 배우 이명행의 성범죄 사실을 알고도 연극 <거미여인의 키스>에 캐스팅 하였으며, 해당 사실에 대해 입장문 및 제대로 된 사과문 하나 없이 사명만 변경, 변경 후 첫 작품인 <나쁜자석>에 미투 운동을 조롱한 배우 이기현을 캐스팅하였습니다. 해당 캐스팅에 대해 제작사 측에서는 모르쇠로 일관하다 연이은 관객들의 지적이 있고 나서야 사과문 아닌 사과문을 게시하였고, 반성과 함께 신중히 작품 제작에 임하겠다는 입장을 표명하였습니다. 이는 결국 반성하겠다는 것은 말 뿐, 해당 배우의 기용에는 변함이 없다는 입장이며 금일(16일) 오전 11시 오픈 예정인 1차 티켓 스케줄에서도 해당 배우가 확인되었습니다.

오는 1월 23일, 이명행에 대한 1심 판결이 나옵니다. 이명행의 성폭력 피해 사실을 고발하고 1년. 아직도 피해자들은 고통을 받고 있습니다.

제대로 된 사과 없이 미래가 이어지진 않습니다.
한 사람의 힘은 작아보일지 모르나 이미 많은 관객들이 <나쁜자석>과 제작사 레드앤블루의 작품을 불매하겠다는 의지를 보이고 있습니다. 그리고 저 또한 공연예술을 사랑하는 한 사람의 관객으로서, 미약하나마 피해자들과 연대하며 정당하고 올바른 미래가 정립되길 바라기에 <나쁜자석>을 불매합니다.

오는 1월 23일, 이명행에 대한 1심 판결이 나옵니다. 이명행의 성폭력 피해 사실을 고발하고 1년. 아직도 피해자들은 고통을 받고 있습니다.

text:
dear brave heart... i know you have been hurt.
and i know you have fear. 
that's normal. 
but i want to encourage you with this:
run to god.
climb up on his lap. 
give him all your burdens.
release all your worries.
bury yourself in his arms of love.
because his love for you is perfect.
and perfect love casts out all fear. 
and when fear disappears, so will control. 
i promise you, if you run to god?
your mind and body will fill up with hope.
and hope brings us joy.
and joy?
well, it brings us healthiness! 😍💜🙌
love.... #metoo

according to the survey of inmates of state correctional facilities by the u.s. department of justice bureau of justice statistics. * those inmates who were convicted of committing violent acts against children were more like to have been white, a percentage of nearly 70%, than any other race. * white inmates were nearly three times more likely to have victimized a child than black inmates. ⬇️

85% of people are stalked by someone they know. 
visit our website (link in our bio) for resources.

text:
how they used dr. mlk to decieve the world! #facts
orgies among the congregation 
among its other accusations are that:

dr king took part in "drunken sex orgies" and coerced young women to participate

he had love affairs with at least four women, including folk singer joan baez

the list of alleged indiscretions would likely have been deeply problematic for the civil rights leader if it had been made public in 1968.
⬇️
according to the survey of inmates of state correctional facilities by the u.s. department of justice bureau of justice statistics. * those inmates who were convicted of committing violent acts against children were more like to have been white, a percentage of nearly 70%, than any other race. * white inmates were nearly three times more likely to have victimized a child than black inmates. ⬇️
according to rainn (rape, abuse and incest national network) and the bureau of justice, 57% of all sexual violence perpetrators are white males.
⬇️
according to suicide prevention expert, dr. christine moutier, white, middle-aged men account for 70% of deaths from suicide each year. nine-tenths of them are from a lower socioeconomic classthese are being called “deaths of despair.”harvard public policy professor robert d. putnam, told the bbc, "this is part of the larger emerging pattern of evidence of the links between poverty, hopelessness and health.” veterans are often one of the largest segments within this group. according to a 2014 veterans affairs (va) report, 20 commit suicide each day. 65% of them are age 50 or older. a larger segment of this group has chosen the slow suicide.

text:
ich habe in den letzten monaten einige bücher gelesen, die mich persönlich sehr berührt haben. 
vor ein paar tagen habe ich mir dann das buch „nein“ von winnie m li gekauft. 
die geschichte von vivian ist winnie m lis geschichte. schonungslos erzählt sie davon, wie eine einzige begegnung das ganze leben verändern kann- und geht noch einen schritt weiter: sie schreibt zugleich die geschichte des mannes auf, für den das wort nein nichts zählt.
die autoren gehört zu den gefragtesten stimmen in der #metoo-debatte. 
warum ich euch dieses buch unbedingt ans herz legen möchte: weil viele außenstehende denken, dass mit einer anzeige der horror ein ende hat. für viele opfer beginnt aber leider erst mit der anzeige der mentale kampf. 
wenn euch betroffene manchmal suspekt vorkommen, dann solltet ihr dieses buch lesen um ein kleinen einblick in ihr leben zu bekommen. das buch ist ziemlich nah an der realität geschrieben.
(unbezahlte werbung wegen verlags- und autorennennung)

text:
from 1 february 2019, we will be holding free weekly employment drop in sessions: ⁣
⁣⁣
fridays: 12pm - 5pm⁣
⁣
how we can help you?⁣ ⁣
if you are an employee, agency worker, casual or contract worker, we can assist you in the following areas:⁣ ⁣
• unfair dismissal⁣
• discrimination⁣
• redundancy⁣
• maternity or parental rights⁣
• health and safety, changes in working hours and conditions⁣
• unpaid wages⁣
• bullying⁣
• any other employment-related matter⁣
⁣
if you need further assistance (including representing you at a tribunal hearing) after we have advised you at your initial appointment, we will sign-post your case to north kensington law centre. .⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

text:
un poema que encontré por ahí...
mujer
un ser que aún no acaba de ser. no la remota rosa angelical que los poetas cantaron. no la maldita bruja que los inquisidores quemaron. no la temida y deseada prostituta. no la madre bendita. no la marchita y burlada solterona. no la obligada a ser buena. no la obligada a ser mala. no la que vive porque la dejan vivir. no la que debe siempre decir que sí. un ser que trata de saber quien es y que empieza a existir. ¿es que acaso tememos su bondad, amor, fuerza, inteligencia?
basta de violencia contra la mujer!

brindemos la mano a nuestras hermanas andaluzas. nosotras no negociamos con machistas, no vamos a dar ni un paso atrás en igualdad. 
lo único que vamos a hacer es dar pasos adelante para terminar con el patriarcado. 
mañana tenemos la oportunidad de gritar por los derechos de las andaluzas en las calles, como lo hemos hecho por otras mujeres que han sufrido injusticias en todas partes del mundo. 
no nos van a callar. no tenemos miedo. estamos más unidas que nunca y entre todas vamos a luchar por nuestros derechos. los de las mujeres de todo el mundo.

text:
"is this the best a man can get"? riding in on the coat-tail of the #metoo movement, @gillette has somehow compounded the trivial pursuit that is intersectional feminism, with the mundane tasks of basic male grooming.

https://youtu.be/kopmueyp3a0

the ad (link above) challenges men, boys, blacks, hispanics, pre pubescent teens, or anyone with a swinging penis between their legs to "shave off their toxic masculinity". despite a negative reception, gillette has no plans to pull the ad. in the face of social media backlash, brand director of @gillette america pankaj bhalla has repeatedly dismissed claims the ad paints men in a negative light. “we recognize it’s sparking a lot of passionate dialogue—at the same time, it’s getting people to stop and think about what it means to be our best selves, which is the point of the spot"
-pb

incorporating politically and socially charged issues into brands has become a commonly used marketing tool in what has become the "belief economy". it is however, important to note this is not the first time gillette has attempted to capitalize under the guise of altruism, as the initial gillette fortune was made marketing the safety razor the armed forces.

after patenting the obsolescent design of the safety razor in 1901. the socialist king c. gillette convinced the us military a clean shave was nesseccary to properly form a seel when wearing a gas-mask. king was awarded contract and sold 4.1 millions razors at cost, knowing the real profit would take place when returning soliders needed to replace their dull razors.
