text:
thank you @simonandschuster for this free review copy of good and mad #partner
-
good and mad by rebecca traister
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ | 4 stars
in the year 2018, it seemed as if women’s anger had suddenly erupted into the public conversation. but long before pantsuit nation, the women’s march, and the #metoo movement, women’s anger was not only politically catalytic but politically problematic. the story of female fury and its cultural significance demonstrates the long history of bitter resentment that has enveloped women’s slow rise to political power, as well as the ways that anger is received when it comes from women as opposed to when it comes from men.
in her latest novel, traister evaluates the history of female anger and introduces readers to this compelling force, which, when harnessed, can change history.
-
a great pick for readers who enjoy nonfiction, history, politics, and topics related to feminism and the women’s movement.
-
personally, i didn’t love this book... here’s why:
1) not the style of writing i enjoy reading
2) there was tooooo much detail and information
nonetheless, this is a brilliantly researched and written novel, and the artwork and design are to die for 🤤. if you’re interested in the topics it discusses, pick up a copy.
-

gop is dead. gop remains dead. and we have killed him. how shall we comfort ourselves, the murderers of all murderers? what was holiest and mightiest of all that the world has yet owned has bled to death under our knives: who will wipe this blood off us? what water is there for us to clean ourselves? what festivals of atonement, what sacred games shall we have to invent? is not the greatness of this deed too great for us? must we ourselves not become gods simply to appear worthy of it?

howlindsey doody

text: um dos factores perversos no racismo e na xenofobia é estigmatizar um grupo de pessoas pelo comportamento de alguns indivíduos pertencentes a esse grupo. o ódio e o preconceito alimentam-se disso. de se achar que os ciganos são todos ladrões, os alentejanos são preguiçosos, as brasileiras são todas putas, por aí fora. o #metoo, por mais méritos iniciais que tenha tido, transformou-se nisto: numa caça às bruxas, na diabolização da masculinidade, no pânico infundado da generalização de comportamentos que a esmagadoríssima maioria dos homens condena veementemente. por mais bem intencionado que este anúncio possa ter sido imaginado (o que sinceramente duvido...), não passa de uma profunda agressão aos homens. e eu acho que os homens não têm de pedir desculpa por serem homens. já chega.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

.
.
gentry started writing this before the #metoo movement came about but as we know, harassment and victimization has been happening long before. a book that will not be for everyone but i like the raw manner in which gentry writes and have since good as gone. 🖤
.
.
full and long thoughts on my goodreads and upcoming #atbr2019 blog post. 👩🏻‍💻 #wtrgreviews .
.
“dana diaz is an aspiring stand‑up comedian—a woman in a man’s world. when she meets a tough computer programmer named amanda dorn, the two bond over their struggles in boys’ club professions. dana confides that she’s recently been harassed and assaulted while in l.a., and amanda comes up with a plan: they should go after each other’s assailants,  strangers on a train–style. but dana finds that revenge, however sweet, draws her into a more complicated series of betrayals. soon her distrust turns to paranoia, encompassing strangers, friends—and even herself. at what cost will she get her vengeance? who will end up getting hurt? and when it’s all over, will there be anyone left to trust?”
.

text:
i can't say that i differ as much in those specific years, emotion wise, what i can say is, i went from being a super happy child, to being a suicidal extremely depressed teen. constant criticism, bullying, blackmail and being used for various reasons made me feel less than dog shit. in the first 2 photos i was caring, loving, happy and most of all, naive... my experiences made me hard and cold, full of trust issues and hate for other people... it is only recently that i started letting people in again, being able to trust people, give my fullest to the people i care about and being able to stand my ground without being a psycho bitch about it (my coping method after everything i've been through), not editing my photos and now embracing who i am. it is only now that i can say with true honesty that i am happy again. what other people think of me is their problem, how i live my life is completely my choice and my mental health is my responsibility to look after.

#10yearchallenge #mylife #antibully #suicidesurvivor #beyou #beyourself #behappy #lovelife #loveyourself #inspiration #storyofmylife #stopbullying #metoo #bekind #selfharmrecovery #mentalhealth

text: today is the day!!!! my new book choose life is released today! i’m so happy 😀 choose life is an educational and awareness practical self-help workbook for survivors of childhood sexual abuse and it can be used to by organisations or groups that work with survivors of childhood sexual abuse!  you may not have been through it but the chances are you know someone in your family, social circle or even at work that has been through it, why not support them in buying this book as a gift? my book is available on amazon in uk and america,barnes & noble, and other retailers around the world. also it will be available soon on waterstones online. now the hard work of getting my book out there begins and that includes getting it into book stores. got some interviews coming up as well. i’m nervous but excited at the same time because i’ve never done an educational book before but now i can say i have done it😃 i have taken another step out my comfort zone and it’s the best feeling💯 i hope those for who i have wrote the book for feel empowered by what i share! let the journey to get my book out there begin!💯😀 #chooselife #book #empowerment #education #awareness #self-help #sexualabuse #childhoodsexualabuse #author #visionary #leader #empoweringpeople #empoweredlife #lovingpeople #metoo #amazon #risk #stepoutmycomfortzone
name: The Empowered Life

text:
《all about consent》- die #metoo-debatte hat zu einer größeren öffentlichen aufmerksamkeit zum thema zustimmung / einverständnis beigetragen und liz kleinrock, #grundschullehrerin in kalifornien, hat daraus eine #unterrichtseinheit für #kinder entwickelt. ich habe heute eine deutschsprachige #version davon im sozialen lernen ausprobiert. meine kinder sind 12-13 jahre alt und da ist das thema "#berührung" natürlich mit viel aufregung belegt. umso wichtiger, sich bewusst zu machen, welches #verhalten richtig ist und welches nicht. es kam mehrmals mit leuchtenden augen die frage, ob man im #comic (15 min zeit nur) auch zeigen dürfe, wie man jemand zu etwas zwingt. meine antwort? - "was hast du in der stunde heute gelernt? wie man jemand zu etwas zwingt? nein?! dann zeichnest du es auch nicht." es ist so wichtig, kindern klar zu sagen, was geht - und was nicht. ihr ausloten der anwendungsmöglichkeiten miteinander hat direkt nach der stunde begonnen, nämlich wenn es um das ausleihen von materialien ging. und die lustige #tee-analogie auf youtube ist 100% so eindrucksvoll 😅, dass das thema sie noch eine weile begleiten wird. 
#consent #tea #noisno #yesisyes #neinheißtnein #sozialeslernen #ethik #schule #berlin  #lizkleinrock  @teachandtransform #teachersofinstagram #lehrerzimmer #instalehrerzimmer

کالایی که مانند اپل و ..باید در بالاترین کیفیت به #مرد عرضه بشه❗
.

حالا کمپانی های عظیم مد ،#آرایش، #جراحی های افسارگسیخته ، انواع و اقسام #کاشت_ناخن تا #زیورآلات مچ پا تا آرایش ساق پا کشیدگی پوست و خالکوبی، برداشتن چربی پهلو، عمل لیفت سینه و بازو، #تزریق_ژل تو اندام و بوتاکس و پروتز لب و چاله چونه، #اکستنشن و هزاران بدبختی و عذاب در قالب#مدرنیته یا همون جاهلیت ثانی، سر جنس #ریحانه و لطیف زن میارن که چرخ ابر کمپانی ها بچرخه😑
.

و یا زن رو به نیروی کار ارزان،منشی یا کارگر برای کاهش هزینه تبدیل کنه.
بعد زن رو در یک رقابت ناتمام با همجنس خودش برای ظاهری بهتر داشتن قرار میدن که در آن احدی برنده نیست✋
.
وقتی که باید صرف تعالی و سیر به سمت ملکوت بشه،صرف این چیزا میشه..❗
زنی که میتونه مادری بشه که #محسن_حججی  بپروره
حالا امثال وحید خزائی تربیت میکنه❗
.

بعد چشم که باز میکنی میبینی چهره زن امروز با انجام تمام این کارهای کثیف غربی، از حالت عادیه عاطفی خود به یک عروسک زشت مصنوعی و بدون #عاطفه که صرفاً با فیزیک خود معرفی میشه شناخته شده❌
.

یعنی با زدن حجاب، چنان بلایی به سر #زن آوردن که زن امروز نیازمند یک مُنجیه...
.
.

این میشه که:👇
پولساز ترین #سلبریتی‌ های غرب مثل #لیدی_گاگا رو فرش قرمز با کت مردونه سایز بزرگ میاد که بگه من آلت دست نیستم❌
.

هشتگ های جهانی#metoo در نفی #تجاوز راه میوفته❌
.

در کره کمپین های نابودی لوازم آرایش، تظاهرات #حقوق_زنان رخ میده، مردم پلاکارد بالای سر خودشون میگیرن که my life is not your porn ❌
.
.

لطفا بیایید از این به بعد چنین تفکری رو رواج بدیم که:👇
زن با حجاب، ناخودآگاه به تمام پیرامون اینو القا میکنه که من ارزشمندم و مستحق احترام👌
.

و در کنار الگو نشان دادن #حضرت_زهرا_س و #حضرت_زینب_س ، از شواهد عینی برای این افراد مثال بزنید که مثلا
نگاهی به کره بنداز..
این از #هالیوود..
این از دختره که رفت سیرجان و زیر دست و پا بود،
این از تجاوزات در سوئد
و...
.

و بگید لازمه بدونی مردایی که از حقوق و ازادیه جسم تو میگن،مزخرف میگن..
اینا تو رو کالا میبینن و برهنه و دم دست و ذلیل میخوانت..
حالا دیگه خوددانی✋

stop_filter_tweet: ظرتون؟🤔 . به نظر شما اگر نباشه چی میشه؟ . به نظر من زنی که بهش گفتن حجاب و بزار کنار، یعنی اندام تو نشون بده بدون تعارف😑 . حالا که زن ابتدای مسیر بی انتهای ظاهرگرایی و افتاد، حالا که افتاد تو دام که معتقد به این است که در عالم تمام پدیده ها کالا و قابل خرید و فروش هستند دیگه زن به عنوان کالا تلقی میشه❗ . کالایی که مانند اپل و ..باید در بالاترین کیفیت به عرضه بشه❗ . حالا کمپانی های عظیم مد ، های افسارگسیخته ، انواع و اقسام تا مچ پا تا آرایش ساق پا کشیدگی پوست و خالکوبی، برداشتن چربی پهلو، عمل لیفت سینه و بازو، تو اندام و بوتاکس و پروتز لب و چاله چونه، و هزاران بدبختی و عذاب در قالب یا همون جاهلیت ثانی، سر جنس و لطیف زن میارن که چرخ ابر کمپانی ها بچرخه😑 . و یا زن رو به نیروی کار ارزان،منشی یا کارگر برای کاهش هزینه تبدیل کنه . بعد زن رو در یک رقابت ناتمام با همجنس خودش برای ظاهری بهتر داشتن قرار میدن که در آن احدی برنده نیست✋ . وقتی که باید صرف تعالی و سیر به سمت ملکوت بشه،صرف این چیزا میشه..❗ زنی که میتونه مادری بشه که بپروره حالا امثال وحید خزائی تربیت میکنه❗ . بعد چشم که باز میکنی میبینی چهره زن امروز با انجام تمام این کارهای کثیف غربی، از حالت عادیه عاطفی خود به یک عروسک زشت مصنوعی و بدون که صرفاً با فیزیک خود معرفی میشه شناخته شده❌ . یعنی با زدن حجاب، چنان بلایی به سر آوردن که زن امروز نیازمند یک مُنجیه ... . . این میشه که : 👇 پولساز ترین های غرب مثل رو فرش قرمز با کت مردونه سایز بزرگ میاد که بگه من آلت دست نیستم❌ . هشتگ های جهانی در نفی راه میوفته❌ . در کره کمپین های نابودی لوازم آرایش، تظاهرات رخ میده، مردم پلاکارد بالای سر خودشون میگیرن که life porn ❌ . . لطفا بیایید از این به بعد چنین تفکری رو رواج بدیم که : 👇 زن با حجاب، ناخودآگاه به تمام پیرامون اینو القا میکنه که من ارزشمندم و مستحق احترام👌 . و در کنار الگو نشان دادن و ، از شواهد عینی برای این افراد مثال بزنید که مثلا نگاهی به کره بنداز.. این از الیوود.. این از دختره که رفت سیرجان و زیر دست و پا بود، این از تجاوزات در سوئد و ... . و بگید لازمه بدونی مردایی که از حقوق و ازادیه جسم تو میگن،مزخرف میگن.. اینا تو رو کالا میبینن و برهنه و دم دست و ذلیل میخوانت.. حالا دیگه خوددانی✋

text:
『８２年生まれ、キム・ジヨン』、読了~

祖母、母、１９８２年生まれの主人公の女性の人生をなぞって、
１９８２年から２０１５年の女性の地位を描く小説というか、小説らしくない小説。

おそらくその時代を生きた女性の誰もが、
どれかは経験している経験を集めて
ジヨンを書いています。

就職できないジヨンに対する、父親と母親のやりとり。 「手伝う」という言葉についてのジヨンの捉え方。

友人に対するセクハラについての職場でのやりとり。

そうそう！と頷いてしまう言葉、文章。

ラストを読んで、「男性」に対して、はあーーーとため息をついてしまいました😢
（いや、小説としては、上手なラストですが）

でも、解説を最後まで読み、私自身にもバイアスがあることがわかりました。読んでよかった。。。 韓国で１００万部売れたという本書、日本でも、読まれますように。
多くの女性の未来のために✨

text:
this past week, hiking through griffith park wouldn’t have felt so freeing if i hadn’t experienced the pain of being controlled. the sunset over the pacific ocean wouldn’t have looked as beautiful if i hadn’t experienced the ugliness of abuse. most of all, my time with family and friends wouldn’t have felt so cherished and precious if i hadn’t experienced six years of loneliness and isolation.
.
god is omnipotent. he has the power to give us a painless life, but because he is omniscient, he sees that he’d be robbing us of the most beautiful joy we could feel in the good times. i was beautifully and wonderfully made, but i can see that god, through his omniscience, is continuing to craft me every day through the good, the bad, and the ugly. and i wouldn’t have it any other way because it’s god’s way.
.
recently, so many exciting but scary, uncomfortable, and difficult opportunities have presented themselves. but i believe in myself now, and i can do hard things. and i can’t wait to see how god crafts me through those experiences.
.
i can do all things through christ, who gives me strength. -philippians 4:13
.
.
.
.
.
#godsway #friendsarethebest #friendsandfamily #metoo #philippians413 #icandohardthings #beautifullyandwonderfullymade #believeinyourself #believe #youcandoit

text:
“boys will be boys.” gentlemen…we need to talk. *deep breath* i’ve got issues with gillette. primarily why they charge so damn much for their razors. that’s one of the main reasons why i grew a beard to begin with.

if i was the kind who wore hats, i’d take mine off to gillette for the video they’ve released.

called “we believe: the best men can be” is directed toward the bullying and harassment in our world. it’s presented in an intelligent manner that was intended to begin a conversation. 
after i watched the video - which is only 1:48 in length - i felt so inspired. it’s marketing to be sure - gillette’s slogan for many years has been “the best a man can get.” but it’s a great video that left me moved and inspired.

until i read the comments…

the most common refrain was either: “my wife’s boyfriend loves this video.” and some sort of refrain on feeling attacked and interpreting the video as anti-male/anti-man.

how insecure do you have to be to see that as the case? c’mon y’all!

i believe we’re all generally good. men and women. we all want to feed our families and raise our children in a healthy way. but the high-profile examples of men like roy moore, harvey weinstein, bill cosby, and r kelly cast a light on all of us. and the light isn’t exactly pure, y’know?

are we all peasants? absolutely not!

but we can all play a part in ensuring that the next harvey, bill, r, or roy (or louis or donald, or kevin, or millions of others) don’t happen. fathers can provide a healthy masculine example to their kids. 
be kings! it’s not that friggin’ hard! quit being so fucking cynical. grow up and be a king!

long story short, if you were offended by that video then you’re exactly the people the ad was directed toward. “boys will be boys.” - this is absolutely right. but men can help those boys grow up to be better men! that’s all the ad was talking about.

we can all be better. all be better.

text:
det är inte alla tiotusentals metoo-vittnesmål under hösten 2017 som kommer att förändra verkligheten till det bättre.

det som kommer att göra den stora skillnaden, som kommer att berättas om i framtida historieböcker, är om vi lyckas hålla fast i frågan, ha kvar den på vår dagordning och se till att vi genomför konkreta samhällsförändringar.

arbetsgivare, chefer och ledare i samhällets alla (!) sektorer, är enligt sveriges rikes lag, skyldiga att bedriva ett förebyggande arbete för att kunna motverka sexuella trakasserier.

dessvärre har okunskapen bland just ansvariga om vad lagen säger varit utbredd.

därför utlovade jag landets alla chefer ett utbildningsverktyg som nu har lanserats. finn det via länken i bion.

ingen ska kunna skylla på att man inte har kunskap om vad lagen säger eller inte vet hur man ska förebygga brott.

tipsa din närmsta chef och dela detta med din vänner. vi tar ännu ett steg i rätt riktning ✊🏽🌍.
.
#syntolkning: har en telefon med webbverktyget för alla chefer i min hand.
.
#svpol #metoo #do #arbetsmiljöverket

text:
kelly wants vengeance in court. 
r. kelly’s life has been in shambles ever since the lifetime series surviving r. kelly debuted. the docuseries explored kelly’s sexual history, which is riddled with accusations of sexual, mental, and physical assault. over 50 people were interviewed, and the long list of accusations has turned the world against r. kelly. artists he wrote songs for or collaborated with are shunning him, while two cities are asking witnesses and victims to come forward so a proper investigation can be done. radio stations are starting to ban kells music, and it appears the legend is about to watch his entire legacy disappear before his eyes. 
according to tmz, sources close to kells are claiming that he is not worried about the artists that are cutting him off and disowning him. he is dismissing artists like lady gaga, b2k, celine dion, and others as “phonies” who are desperate to look good in the public eye. on the other hand. kells is completely freaking out about surviving r. kelly. he sent a cease and desist letter to lifetime days before they aired the series, demanding that it be shelved. now, kells is doing everything in his power to strike back at lifetime. tmz reports he has been attempting to find dirt on executives who work for the network while he also works with a legal team to dissect the content in the docuseries.

text: last week, the american psychological association (apa) released a first-ever report entitled "guidelines for the psychological practice with boys and men"... the report defines "masculine ideaology" as "a constellation of standards that have held sway over large segments of the male population including: anti-femininity, achievement, eschual of the appearance of weakness, and adventure risk and violence"... further, the report says that "traditional masculinity ideology has been shown to limit males' psychological development, constrain their behavior, result in gender role strain and gender role conflict and negatively influence mental and physical health"... the report also says that "conforming to the norms of "masculine ideology" can result in suppressing and masking distress in young boys as well as more risk-taking and aggressive behavior and an unwillingness to seek out help...this can lead to traits like homophobia and pave the way for sexual harassment, bullying and violence against others and themselves"... their conclusion: "traditional masculinity (i.e., "toxic masculinity") - marked by stoicism, competitiveness, dominance and aggression - is, on the whole, harmful"...what is blatantly absent in the report is a consensus definition for what it means to be a man...where is the line drawn on acceptable versus unacceptable male behavior?...i am a strong advocate for women's rights and fully support progressive movements such as #metoo and #timesup but to have a major professional organization like the apa, which i am a lifetime member of, advocate behaviors that they recklessly deem "harmful" is to further blur the increasingly fuzzy lines that distinguish the sexes...and to broad-brush many very normal male behaviors as "harmful" is irresponsible, unethical, and most of all, in my opinion, unconscionable...the above commercial was recently released by a major us corporation, gillette...it displays selective behaviors of some boys and men which are clearly wrong and unacceptable yet the implication is that this is the way the majority of men think and behave...my rebuttal of the apa report is pending...and, as of today, i'm a converted schick man...

text:
i’ve been thinking about this so much in the last few years since giving birth to my daughters. i know i won’t be able to shield them from everything, and if i’m completely honest with myself i don’t want to. i know then will have close calls, awkward situations, and make a few poor life choices. but one thing i want most for them is to always feel empowered to say “no”.
because i wasn’t.
i didn’t know how to express my discomfort, to get help, to use my voice. i was so worried about making a scene or causing a stir that far too many times i stayed silent. or even worse the awkward uncomfortable laugh. you know the one. where you’re dying in the inside, desperately want to run but just laugh and hope the moment passes.
the laugh that comes out in “harmless” work exchanges, ass grabs, dirty words and peer pressure. the laugh that any other woman can instantly recognize from across the room. the laugh that makes your skin crawl because you know how horrible she feels in that moment.
so how do i empower my girls to say “no”? what does this actually look like in practice?
a few ideas...
letting them say “no” to us as parents. more importantly respecting it when they do.
providing them bodily autonomy and respecting the shit out of it. teaching them to stay connected to their bodies and encourage them to express how they feel on the regular. openly and without judgement.
what are some other ways we can empower our girls to say “no”?
•
#consciousparenting
#feminist
#metoo
#raisinggirls

my he”art” “same girl different faces”
working on this new project, this is part two from my last posting of “same girl different faces” just trying to figure out how i’m going to incorporate it into one project! i love the different personalities of this individual, which by the way is the same person that can have either: ptsd, bipolar, multiple personalities or identity disorder. regarding this project i’m working on lovers, as long as you wake up in the morning & face yourself in the mirror every day & accept yourself for who you are, then there is no need to explain to the outer world your story; your story is just that.. your story. “every flower must grow through dirt.”- jo offduty.

text:
cuando hace unas semanas, en argentina se revolvió todo con la declaración de abuso de una de las actrices de patito feo, pensé que quizás había llegado el momento de que me atreviera a salir de mi cortina y a hacer parte de esta fuerza que se ha creado entre todas las mujeres que tenían esa profunda herida... por primera vez estoy siendo capaz de coger este dolor y transformarlo en fuerza para intentar cambiar algunas cosas.
cosas que desgraciadamente hemos normalizado todas en nuestra sociedad, yo la primera, porque a lo largo de mi vida,  me ha pasado más de una vez, y he hecho como si nada... pero ya no, ya no estoy detrás de esa cortina... ya he cogido la fuerza para intentar poner mi granito de arena en este cambio! 
y sobre todo he cogido la fuerza para quererme, para querer a esa flavia de 13 años a la que le pasó, (y a todas las de después), fuerza para perdonarme.... ahora soy capaz de coger mi herida y sentirme fuerte, porque además sé que no estoy sola en esto!
#miracomonosponemos #metoo
name: Flavia
tweet_full:
cuando hace unas semanas, en argentina se revolvió todo con la declaración de abuso de una de las actrices de patito feo, pensé que quizás había llegado el momento de que me atreviera a salir de mi cortina y a hacer parte de esta fuerza que se ha creado entre todas las mujeres que tenían esa profunda herida... por primera vez estoy siendo capaz de coger este dolor y transformarlo en fuerza para intentar cambiar algunas cosas.
cosas que desgraciadamente hemos normalizado todas en nuestra sociedad, yo la primera, porque a lo largo de mi vida,  me ha pasado más de una vez, y he hecho como si nada... pero ya no, ya no estoy detrás de esa cortina... ya he cogido la fuerza para intentar poner mi granito de arena en este cambio! 
y sobre todo he cogido la fuerza para quererme, para querer a esa flavia de 13 años a la que le pasó, (y a todas las de después), fuerza para perdonarme.... ahora soy capaz de coger mi herida y sentirme fuerte, porque además sé que no estoy sola en esto!
#miracomonosponemos #metoo

text:
have you ever felt like being you is not good enough? you don’t have what other people have? and if only, you were more beautiful.. your life would have been sooo much better?
.
i often find myself feeling that way. in which i shouldn’t. i am more than enough and i don’t need to be like someone else or own things that they own. the best version of me that i can be is being unapologetically myself; comfortable in my perfect imperfection.
.
so this is to the girls and women who go through everyday of their lives, wishing you were someone else: being yourself is the most phenomenal thing you can be. 💜✨💭
.
#timetotalk19 #womensempowerment #wemeanpower #metoo #likeagirl #timesup #timesupnow #women #girls #insecure #instagram #who

text:
doy las gracias a los que han estado a mi lado, ayudándome a abrir los ojos y a cicatrizar mi herida, respetando mi silencio y mis tiempos. 
también le doy las gracias a mi familia por haberme escuchado hoy, y entender por qué en su momento no fui capaz de hablar...
sé que en mi silencio de años, ha habitado también el silencio de muchas.
sólo espero, que al igual que todas las publicaciones de las argentinas, a mi, me han dado el valor; mi publicación le haya dado el valor, al menos a una, para quizás, salir también ella de detrás de la cortina... en especial, quiero dar las gracias a @anscarrasco por su ayuda incondicional en esto (y en todo). y gracias a mi, por haber encontrado esta valentía, que tenía tan escondida dentro de mi cuerpo🌸
#metoo #miracomonosponemos

text:
ever since i told my sexual assault story, so many women have come to me with their #metoo moments. they have trusted me with stories they have hidden inside of them for far too long. this is for all of you brave women.

you are worthy. 
you were worthy of and deserved protection back then and you are worthy of it now. not because you are weak. heaven knows you are a survivor. because you are powerful and precious. you have a heart for infinite creation, you are divinity in human form, you are a world changer. 
you are valuable, just as you are. 
#recognizeyourworth #bestillandknow #illuminatefromwithin #youmatter

text:
having handled sexual assault cases for years, it’s blown my mind how undervalued and ignored rape is. well not anymore. “they said a little black girl from clayton county is worth a billion dollars.” this meant the world to me for what it stands for and the impact it will have on sexual assault cases. to have the highest verdict in us history for a single victim is humbling. (common questions- no this wasn’t luck, i explained my argument on value to them. and is my 3rd record jury verdict for a rape. yes, it’s a real 12 juror verdict. no, the jury wasn’t all black. yes, black girls are victims disproportionately for assault.  yes, consultations are confidential.) #speakup

text:
📸📸📸
from ➡️ @mrtrut ☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆
друзья, привет! 👋

вдохновение приходит по-разному. 
иногда, ты четко, с нуля, выстраиваешь определенную концепцию и собираешь её по крупицам мозаики, продумываешь легенды и оставляешь пасхалки. 
но!👆🏻 бывает так: совершенно случайно, ты знакомишься с чьим-либо творчеством или личностью, мгновенно понимаешь, на сколько это сильно и важно (в том числе и для тебя). сразу хочешь рассказать об этом кому-то ещё. 
круто, когда у тебя есть ресурс и желание, а главное - возможность реализовывать это в своей работе, ведь, тогда ты и сам кайфуешь, вдохновение, будто, переполняет тебя и ты готов делиться этим со всеми!🙌 твигги 🍸

коктейль назван в честь знаменитой модели твигги, символа моды 60-х. икона стиля для своих современников и легендарная личность для последующих поколений моделей.

в стилистике этот коктейль - твист на ”clover club” ⠀⠀
•джин (@sipsmith )настоянный на чае «малина и мята» ⠀⠀
•сок лимона 🍋 ⠀⠀
•мёд «алое» 🍯 ⠀⠀
•сироп розы 🌹 ⠀⠀
•белок 🥚

hello friends! 👋

inspiration comes in different ways.
sometimes, you clearly, from scratch, build a certain concept and collect it in pieces of a mosaic, think up legends and leave easter eggs.
but! 👆🏻 it happens like this: completely by chance, you get acquainted with someone's creativity or personality, you instantly understand how strong and important this is (including for you). just want to tell someone else about it.
cool, when you have the resource and desire, and most importantly - the opportunity to realize it in your work, because then you yourself get high, the inspiration seems to overwhelm you and you are ready to share it with everyone! 🙌 
twiggy

the cocktail is named after the famous model twiggy, the symbol of the fashion of the 60s. an icon of style for his contemporaries and a legendary personality for subsequent generations of models.

in style, this cocktail is a twist on “clover club”
• jin (@sipsmith) infused with raspberry and mint tea ⠀⠀
• lemon juice 🍋 ⠀⠀
• aloe honey 🍯 ⠀⠀
• rose syrup 🌹 ⠀⠀
• protein 🥚

follow ➡️ @mrtrut

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text: #10yearchallenge okay so i went a bit crazy but it wouldn't be me if it wasn't over the top so 🤷‍♀️ welcome to the superficial challenge of 2019 😂 however, one thing we should all reflect on is how we've grown as people... in the full length 2005 bodyshot i was on diet pills, the 2004 shot was taken before i went out nye to a house party at which i was sexually assaulted. by a person i knew well and went to school with. i wasn't at 6th form as i left to go to college but it was spread around school (after confiding in someone) and i was bullied because of it called a slut and worse. in the 2009 shot i'm at uni, going through a rollercoaster of anxiety and depression, feeling isolated and again...on diet pills. i'm  happier now. my story is one of many, and mine is probably tame compared to some but it was a journey that has been hard to come through and those events have definitely effected me as a person long term and my trust in people. i'm stronger, happier and finally at peace in my own skin. 2004 vs 2019, 2005 vs 2019 and 2009 vs 2019. #tbt #mua #metoo #girlsthatlift #gettingolder #30something #30s #2009vs2019 #finewine 😂

text:
feminism discussion part 1
.
today i wanted to talk a bit about feminism. the first wave is easily defined by women's fight for voting power. thought of the second wave is often immediately followed by thought of the contraception train. but what idea or struggle is inseparable from this third wave we are now experiencing? what is it all about? or as us philosophers like to say, what is its essence?
.
in my first year of college i sat in on an art history lecture. the lesson focused in part on two visually similar but symbolically distinct paintings. the first - 'sleeping venus' by giorgione, c.1510* - was a nude of a women in a very submissive seductive pose. the second - 'olympia' by edouard manet, 1863 - also very sexual, but displayed a kind of dominance that was very controversial at that time. these artworks for me, although over 150 years old, represent the transition between a more passive role for women, & the kind of female dominance we now see.
.
discussion continued in part 2.
.

.

***photographs used as a modern representation of the two paintings discussed. meant to spark conversation & should not be taken as my view of positive representations of female empowerment. on whether they do/what does constitute a positive representation of female empowerment, i am at present undecided.

in my first year of college i sat in on an a history lecture. the lesson focused in pa on two visually similar but symbolically distinct paintings. the first - 'sleeping venus' by giorgione, c.1510* - was a nude of a women in a very submissive seductive pose. the second - 'olympia' by edouard manet, 1863 - also very sexual, but displayed a kind of domice that was very controversial at that time. these aworks for me, although over 150 years old, represent the transition between a more passive role for women, & the kind of female domice we now see.
.
discussion continued in pa 2.
.
                              ccfemsoc
.

**post pa 1, image 2

photographer

text:
feminism discussion part 2
.
i have caught myself stating that i disliked influencers who claim to be feminists presenting themselves in an overtly sexual manner. i felt that this was not the correct message to send young women about female empowerment. but have i missed the point? is this wave of female empowerment, like 'olympia'**, indivisible from sexual expression & dominance?
.
what exactly is third wave feminism?
.
if you call yourself a feminist it is important to know what that means, or at least, what it means to you. what do you think third wave feminism is about & what campaigns, like #metoo, do you think are a defining feature of this movement? comment below!
.

text:
topic of the week tuesday 💥 
let’s discuss what has been circulating in the media recently - i am sure that you all recognise r kelly, from his music back in the 2000’s - some may have watched the recent docu-series regarding the sexual, physical, emotional, and mental abuse that the young women were subjected to by r kelly - it is sickening to think that a man who stood as a hero and role model to many people, was capable of committing such inhumane acts - this is a harsh reminder that our women all around the world are still being abused, undervalued, disrespected and mistreated - many people involved in this case turned a blind eye and allowed the abuse to continue for many years. people covered up for him because they did want to be that one that spoke up - we must change this culture of keeping silent about issues that need to be brought to light!! survivors and victims rely on us to speak up for them when they are incapable of speaking up for themselves and we must take that responsibility seriously *a person’s life could be saved!!* - 35% of women worldwide have experienced a form of violence in their lifetime. 70% of women have experienced physical or sexual violence from an intimate partner in their lifetime - these figures are shocking!! we must stand together and fight to protect our women & young girls 
#survivingrkelly #muterkelly #metoo #protectourwomen #speakout #better4kenya #thismuststop

text:
jane walker returns for women’s march

book a tour to scotland's whisky distilleries at
www.whiskywheels.scot

#whisky #whiskytour #whiskywheels #tour #scotland #distillery #islay #whiskey #scotch

jane walker, the female version of johnnie walker’s iconic striding man logo, is making a return for the #womenswave women’s march in washington d.c. this weekend.

johnnie walker’s ‘striding woman’ first appeared in march 2018 on limited edition bottles of johnnie walker black label, which were launched to raise awareness of gender equality issues and ‘invite women into the brand’. its introduction caused a wave of backlash from consumers, who viewed jane walker as a gimmick latching onto the #metoo and women’s rights movements.

now the striding woman is making a return on a series of placards being made available for activists to download, print off and display during the women’s march on washington on 19 january.

the signs, all of which feature the jane walker logo, include slogans such as ‘the future is female’, ‘feminist dad’, and ‘with every step we gain momentum’. they have been designed by a range of male and female graphic artists, including monica ahanonu, libby vanderploeg, ali macdonald, edward ubiera, laurène boglio, grace miceli, william de lannoy, bari schechter and laura zalewski.

diageo, brand owner of johnnie walker, said in a press release: ‘these “signs of progress” aim to celebrate the spirit of the women’s movement and are inspired by the work of non-profit brand partners monumental women and she should run – organisations that honour historic women who have paved the way and champion our future female leaders.’

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
many of the guys offended by the gillette advert don't actually look like they need a shave. saying "i hate burned cheeseburgers" doesn't mean you hate all cheeseburgers, or that all cheeseburgers are burned. saying "i hate toxic masculinity" doesn't mean you hate masculinity, or that all masculinity is toxic. you can still be masculine and not have to adhere to old fashioned and virulent tropes. some people will never understand how important it is to change the way some men act and how it reflects on others. all of you soggy boys outraged by a brand man enough to tell other men their behaviour is unacceptable might want to check yourselves. yes it’s a little bit schmaltzy and overwrought but the replies from men who are clearly fragile and terrified of being criticised is proof of how much campaigns like this are needed.

complaining that the advert is bad because it tells men they’re ‘not good enough’ 🤔 welcome to literally every advert ever targeted at women. at least you’re not good enough because of your actions. 
women just suck because of their skin/hair/weight/face.

toxic masculinity is not the problem. 
lack of genuine masculinity is.

#gillette #bullying #metoo ♁

text: “i don’t look like what i’ve been through.” i have true story to tell. if i could take you back 21 years ago, i was an 8 yr old innocent little girl. i ended up missing something though. for 9 years during that time. i missed my childhood. from the time i was 8 years old until i turned 17 yrs of age, i was molested by a man who was supposed to be a role model, a protector, a father figure; my ex-stepfather. many people do not know what i’ve been through as a child. i’m here to speak on it as many times as i can. it used to be hard to tell my story. i am no longer ashamed, or afraid to talk about it. because of this, i’ve become a strong woman, a great mother, & protector of my own. in 2006, he was arrested and was given only 25 years. i don’t get back those 9 years that he took from me. he came up for parole 2 months ago & was denied! this will be his 11th year locked away. i pray that he never gets out. i’m not looking for anyone to feel sorry for me. i’m not asking for sympathy. just know that there are monsters here walking this very ground your children walk! keep your eyes open! children do not feel they have a voice sometimes so that’s where the fear comes into play. i’m am just happy & blessed that i was strong enough to not let this affect me long term. i’ve been through hell & back even through years after this! broken marriage, to losing it all! but...... i’m still here! standing tall! i don’t have anyone to thank but the lord himself!!! #metoo #iamnotalone #thuggizzlecares💜
name: Thuggizzle Cares Inc.

text:
jessica (@beggarsdaughter) was raised in a christian home and grew up going to church amidst the atmosphere of purity movements and the “true love waits” movement. when she was 13 years old, she was exposed to pornography. by the time she was a senior in high school (17 years old), she was full-on addicted to pornography. during this time, she was an active leader in the church, at the top of her classes in school, and engaging in other wholesome activities. she was the picture of the perfect christian girl on the outside, but on the inside she continued her struggling with her addiction to porn. is it okay to watch porn? she’s still a virgin, after all. she’s not having sex, so it must be okay, right? but jessica soon realized that her addiction was getting out of control. she didn’t know how to get help. at the time, there were no available resources for her, for women, to get help with this.

visit titaniapaige.com or click the link in my bio to hear jessica’s story and her wisdom concerning confession and accountability for porn addiction. 
some questions i ask jessica:
• thinking back on how you struggled with addiction to pornography behind closed doors, what was the catalyst that made you seek help?
• where did your first step toward freedom come from then? • what about the gospel and your relationship with god prompted you to share your struggles with pornography addiction with others?
• what are the pros and cons of confessing anonymously?
• what are some of the things you’d like women to know about before they confess? how do they need to prepare their minds?

text:
get ready for another women's march in bergen!
*
in recent years, we have witnessed an unacceptable rhetoric about women, religion, immigration, ethnicity, and climate challenges; and in 2019, we still have many reasons to march: *
#metoo. the inauguration of supreme court judge brett kavanaugh. the abortion act used as a negotiation card here in norway. larry nassar. the inauguration of brazil's new president jair bolsonaro. attacks on female public figures. no to a consent law in norway. the list is long - and we refuse to just stand and watch!
*
we also want to support and honor the nobel peace prize winners of 2018, denis mukwege mukengere and nadia murad, in their fight against the use of rape and sexual violence as a weapon of war.
*
we will send a clear message to the new us administration, to our own administration - and to the rest of the world - that women's rights are human rights, and human rights are women's rights.
*
this is #whyimarch!
*
this year's main subject: the female body under attack.
*
*
#womensmarchbergen #wmb #womensmarch #womenswave #wmb2019 #metoo #timesup #believesurvivors #believewomen

text: in my world, i am beginning to see the softening of the masculine. care and nurturance and open communication; gentleness. my brother always had this quality and the bar was set high for most other men in my life. now i see more of it from my father, my old time male friends, new friends, my son and maybe i will even see it from my ex- husband. something i have been asking for - perhaps since the day i was born. the divine masculine is rising. the shift is here. a thousand times thank you to all those who did the work and continue to; the heavyweights that carry the burden. please note the picture was taken by a friend not on instagram. #divinemasculine #theshift #rishikesh #gangaaarti #themeekshallinherittheearth #metoo #metoomovement

text:
fadime şahindal ve pela atroshi'nin töre cinayetleri sonrası kurulan ve "pela ve fadime'yi asla unutma" ( glöm aldrig pela och fadime) kelimelerinin i̇sveççe baş harflerinden adını alan gapf, "fadime günleri" adındaki anma etkinliklerine bu yıl da devam ediyor. 16 ocak - 20 şubat arasında gerçekleşecek anma etkinliklerinin teması: "kelimelerden eyleme". etkinlik dahilinde i̇sveç'in birçok şehrinde gerçekleşecek konferans ve konuşmalarda töre ve namus cinayetleri ve #metoo hareketi hakkında birçok konuşma yapılacak. etkinliğin facebook sayfası: https://www.facebook.com/events/814497152220353/?ti=cl

fadime galan: 20 ocak 2019 saat 15:00'da 
hem kadına hem de erkeğe karşı uygulanan töre ve namus şiddetine karşı çalışmalar yapan sivil toplum kuruluşu  gapf - glöm aldrig pela och fadime önderliğinde gerçekleştirilecek galada, i̇sveç'in önde gelen sanatçıları ve politikacıları 20 ocak saat 15:00'da berns'te buluşacak. bora serbülent'in de şarkılarıyla yer alacağı etkinlikte daha birçok isim sahne alacak.

etkinlik hakkında daha fazla bilgi almak isterseniz gapf resmi sayfasını ziyaret edebilirsiniz: http://gapf.se/

fadime şahindal kimdir?
7 yaşında isveç'e taşınan fadime, ailesinin istemediği isveçli patrik lindesjö'ye aşık oldu. ailesinden durumu bir süre saklasa bile durumu öğrendiklerinde evlatlıktan reddedilen genç kadın bir süre sonra babası tarafından töre cinayetine kurban gitti. öldürülmesinin üzerinden 17 yıl geçen genç kadının hikayesi birçok kişiye ilham oldu, hakkında kitaplar yazıldı ve birçok anma etkinliği düzenlendi. isveç'te töre cinayetlerinin sembolü olan fadime şahindal öldürüldüğünde 26 yaşındaydı.

@gapf_riksorganisation @boraserbulent #fadimedagarna #fadimegalan #gapf  #glömaldrig_gapf #sterkproduction #erwikcommunication #fadimesahindal #pelaatroshi #metoo #metoomovement

"we believe". it was unilever that first introduced social responsibility into packaged goods advertising with dove's self-esteem project, but procter & gamble grabbed that ball a few years back and have been running with it ever since. that underlying message has gradually been rolling out to different brands, finally reaching gillette on this the 30th anniversary of that long-established brand slogan "the best a man can get". in an age of #metoo and more, grey new york questions many of the existing assumptions about what truly makes for the "best" from men. needless to say, gillette's status remains unchallenged even if casual sexism, bullying, mansplaining and apparently even barbecues are a strict no-no. director kim gehrig does a fine job of corralling the elements: she's become the go-to for these types of campaigns, last seen on that fine "viva la vulva" campaign for essity, featured here late last year. we can only show 60 seconds here so come see us at https://www.adbrands.net for the full film.

text:
https://www.foxnews.com/lifestyle/gillette-addresses-toxic-masculinity-in-new-ad-campaign

gillette yrittää hyödyntää sukupuolisensitiivistä ajanhenkeä ja on lähtenyt mukaan #metoo-agendaan ja muuhun miesvastaiseen mädätykseen. kampanjan retoriikka kuin feministisen puolueen manifestista, ja oikein toksinen maskuliinisuuskin mainittu uudessa mainoksessa. jumalauta mainoksessa joka on suunnattu miehille joilla on riittävä testotaso parrankasvuun. 
ja mikäs siinä, markkinat päättäköön toimiiko tuo strategia vai ei; mainosten sisällöstä rääkyminen ja anteeksipyyntöjen vaatiminen jääköön minun puolestani sosiaalisen oikeuden hörhoille ja kehopositiivisuusaktivisteille. minulle tuo ei toimi. ongelma on vain siinä, että kuluttajana minulle tulee hieman hankalaksi boikotoida gilletteä, koska joudun ajamaan pään paljaaksi höylällä muutaman päivän välein. en suoralta kädeltä tiedä hyvää vaihtoehtoa gilletten terille ja otan mieluusti suosituksia vastaan.

kova jätkä ostaisi partaveitsen tai käyttäisi hiomapaperia. rikas dandymies tai metroseksuaali (onko tuo termi vielä olemassa?) ostaisi hiuslisäkkeen tai hankkisi hyvää kuluttajapalautetta saaneen kestopigmentoinnin. itse en ajatellut mitään noista vaihtoehdoista. kertakäyttöiset halpishöylät joko eivät aja sänkeä lainkaan, ollen näin yhtä hyödyllisiä kuin se kuuluisa neuvostovalmisteinen perseessäsurisija, tai sitten ne vetävät kinkkuleikkeen kokoisia siivuja päänahasta tehden päänhöyläämisestä pahimmillaan skalppeerausta. afron tai heviletin kasvattaminen on sattuneista syistä myöskin poissuljettu vaihtoehto. munkiksikaan en ajatellut ruveta, vaikka siihen kuontaloni malli sopisikin kuin nakutettu.

eli minulla on kuluttajana nyt pienimuotoinen eettinen dilemma. jos ei korvaavaa parempaa höylää löydy, niin olen pakotettu jatkamaan gilletten tukemista. onneksi toisaalta uskon (ja tiedän) heidän olevan pohjimmiltaan vain rahan ja näkyvyyden perässä tuolla mainoksella. eivät he ideologisista syistä ole lähteneet mukaan feministisen agendan tukemiseen, ellei mammonan tavoittelua sitten lasketa omanlaisekseen ideologiaksi.

#moustache 
#fuckgillette 
#kaljupää

text:
in questi anni di pubblicità sessiste ne abbiamo viste parecchie. a volte fa quasi ridere il modo in cui le figure femminili vengono oggettificate nelle pubblicità. mad men ci insegna che il mondo dell'advertising è storicamente sempre stato dominato dagli uomini: sono gli uomini che scrivono le pubblicità, anche quando i prodotti sono rossetti, assorbenti e borsette. ma questo non influisce soltanto sulla donna: anche il maschio rappresentato nella pubblicità è sempre di un certo tipo. forte, risoluto, potente, rude, "che non deve chiedere mai". e questa è naturalmente una visione alterata della realtà maschile.
·
due giorni fa #gillette, l'azienda dei rasoi per intenderci, ha pubblicato un video contro la mascolinità tossica che trovo stupendo. è stato diretto da una donna, kim gehrig - ogni tanto succede che la prospettiva cambi, pazzesco. ritrae uomini che non hanno problemi a mostrarsi sensibili, uomini che non spiegano le cose alle donne, uomini che si oppongono alle molestie verbali per strada. uomini che a volte chiedono, perché, sapete: capita anche a noi. lo trovate qui: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kopmueyp3a0
·
«è davvero questo il meglio che un uomo può essere? non possiamo ignorare la cosa, sta andando avanti da troppo tempo. non possiamo riderci su, tirando fuori le stesse, vecchie scuse: "sono uomini, gli uomini fanno gli uomini". ma qualcosa è finalmente cambiato. e non si tornerà indietro. perché noi crediamo nella parte migliore degli uomini. nel dire la cosa giusta. nel comportarsi nel modo giusto. qualcuno già lo fa, nel grande e nel piccolo. ma "qualcuno" non è sufficiente. perché i ragazzi che guardano oggi saranno gli uomini di domani.»
·
naturalmente il video è già sotto attacco da parte di una moltitudine di persone online che ha già deciso di boicottare gillette, oltre a esponenti e giornalisti di estrema destra. non mi stupisce: è conveniente far rimanere le cose come stanno. è molto, molto più difficile interrogarsi su cosa vuol dire essere uomini e come raggiungere quella definizione.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this quote to me,  is dumb. i didn't get to be 148kg by having fun. i used food and alcohol to mask my emotions and fill voids in my life. i used them as coping mechanisms and i let myself neglect my health and self worth by eating myself to obesity. 
i did it to "protect myself". when i was 18 i was violently sexually assaulted. my vagina and labia was so damaged after my encounter with someone i considered a close friend that i was not able to walk properly for weeks. this all happened when i 'was beautiful'. i was fit and healthy and proud of my body; and now i've spent the last 7+ years eating to hide myself. i never wanted to feel like that again. 
but i'm sick of feeling like this now.  i want to be happy,  and carefree again.  i want to have children and not worry about my health. o.m. you did not ruin my life. i will not let that one night continue to hold me back. 
#watchthisspace💪🔥 #watchmewinbylosing #happymediummovement #weightloss #weightlossjourney #mysexualassaultstory #sexualassault #metoo

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

i understand captain america, joy behard’s decision to embrace socialism and the real american.  my haitian american family has fully embraced the american dream and i have built my life on it on such principles.  i knew i’d be fine, either way, but never knew it was so bad.  my predicament shocks people, but the resistance to standing my ground against it shocks my consciousness.  if my columbia business school mba,  albany law school degree and 6 years practicing law at white & case llp doesn’t entitle me to equal protection what does?  gonna find out... 🧐🤨🤓😎🎁 #thebiglesson of the #theeighties #thenineties #thestonedage #infinityandbeyond #eternity

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: 'silence, like dante's hell, has its concentric circles. first come the internal inhibitions, self-doubts, repressions, confusions, and shame that make it difficult to impossible to speak, along with the fear of being punished or ostracized for doing so. susan brinson, now chair of the philosophy department at dartmouth, was raped in 1990 by a man, a stranger, who called her a whore and told her to shut up before choking her repeatedly, bashing her head with a stone, and leaving her for dead. afterwards she found various problems in talking about the experience: "it was one thing to have decided to speak and write about my rape, but another to find the voice with which to do it. even after my fractured trachea had healed, i frequently had trouble speaking. i was never entirely mute, but i often had bouts of what a friend labelled 'fractured speech' during which i stuttered and stammered, unable to string together a simple sentence without the words scattering like a broken necklace."' rebecca solnit ❤️

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
gillette references toxic masculinity, bullying, and the #metoo movement in their new advert, and it has split opinion online. the short film titled believe, encourages men to be "the best a man can be". also questioning the 'boys will be boys' attitude towards raising boys and girls differently. 
gillette's president, gary coombe has said that 'by holding each other accountable, eliminating excuses for bad behaviour, and supporting a new generation working toward their personal 'best,' we can help create positive change that will matter for years to come'.
what do you think about the divisive advert?

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn
